1
00:00:20,015 --> 00:00:25,019
Subtitles by explosiveskull
Resync by GoldenBeard

2
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,533
This is the Asgardian

3
00:00:27,536 --> 00:00:30,004
refugee vessel Statesman.

4
00:00:32,707 --> 00:00:34,009
We are under assault.

5
00:00:34,011 --> 00:00:36,408
I repeat,
we are under assault.

6
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:39,978
The engines are dead,
life support failing.

7
00:00:39,981 --> 00:00:43,283
Requesting aid
from any vessel within range.

8
00:00:43,284 --> 00:00:47,286
We are 22 jump points
out of Asgard.

9
00:00:47,289 --> 00:00:49,856
Our crew is made up
of Asgardian families.

10
00:00:49,857 --> 00:00:51,591
We have
very few soldiers here.

11
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:53,560
This is not a warcraft.

12
00:00:53,561 --> 00:00:55,564
I repeat,
this is not a warcraft.

13
00:01:08,944 --> 00:01:11,947
Hear me and rejoice.

14
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:18,051
You have had the privilege

15
00:01:18,052 --> 00:01:20,789
of being saved
by the Great Titan.

16
00:01:23,759 --> 00:01:25,926
You may think
this is suffering.

17
00:01:27,094 --> 00:01:28,295
No.

18
00:01:29,329 --> 00:01:31,599
It is salvation.

19
00:01:35,503 --> 00:01:39,337
Universal scales
tip toward balance

20
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:40,942
because of your sacrifice.

21
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,043
Smile.

22
00:01:45,378 --> 00:01:47,513
For even in death,

23
00:01:47,515 --> 00:01:49,884
you have become
Children of Thanos.

24
00:02:05,432 --> 00:02:07,468
I know what it's like to lose.

25
00:02:09,603 --> 00:02:12,573
To feel so desperately
that you're right...

26
00:02:13,373 --> 00:02:15,977
yet to fail, nonetheless.

27
00:02:24,051 --> 00:02:25,752
It's frightening.

28
00:02:27,022 --> 00:02:28,990
Turns the legs to jelly.

29
00:02:31,091 --> 00:02:33,394
But I ask you, to what end?

30
00:02:34,728 --> 00:02:37,397
Dread it, run from it...

31
00:02:38,432 --> 00:02:40,867
destiny arrives all the same.

32
00:02:42,038 --> 00:02:43,903
And now, it's here.

33
00:02:44,572 --> 00:02:46,439
Or should I say...

34
00:02:47,707 --> 00:02:49,343
I am.

35
00:02:54,647 --> 00:02:55,949
You talk too much.

36
00:02:57,185 --> 00:02:59,050
The Tesseract.

37
00:02:59,052 --> 00:03:01,354
Or your brother's head.

38
00:03:05,893 --> 00:03:08,395
I assume you have
a preference.

39
00:03:09,597 --> 00:03:10,896
Oh, I do.

40
00:03:13,167 --> 00:03:14,367
Kill away.

41
00:03:29,616 --> 00:03:30,683
All right, stop!

42
00:03:34,153 --> 00:03:36,454
We don't have the Tesseract.

43
00:03:36,456 --> 00:03:38,091
It was destroyed on Asgard.

44
00:03:48,968 --> 00:03:51,838
You really are
the worst brother.

45
00:03:56,911 --> 00:03:58,944
I assure you, brother...

46
00:03:58,945 --> 00:04:01,014
the sun will shine
on us again.

47
00:04:02,883 --> 00:04:06,151
Your optimism is misplaced,
Asgardian.

48
00:04:06,152 --> 00:04:10,254
Well, for one thing,
I'm not Asgardian.

49
00:04:10,257 --> 00:04:11,456
And for another...

50
00:04:13,826 --> 00:04:15,060
we have a Hulk.

51
00:04:26,273 --> 00:04:29,043
Let him have his fun.

52
00:05:21,295 --> 00:05:22,862
Allfathers...

53
00:05:24,764 --> 00:05:27,966
let the dark magic flow
through me one last...

54
00:05:28,834 --> 00:05:29,901
time.

55
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,151
That was a mistake.

56
00:05:52,057 --> 00:05:53,793
No!

57
00:06:02,901 --> 00:06:05,605
You're going to die for that.

58
00:06:08,708 --> 00:06:09,875
Shh.

59
00:06:16,815 --> 00:06:18,617
My humble personage...

60
00:06:19,951 --> 00:06:22,187
bows before your grandeur.

61
00:06:25,624 --> 00:06:29,125
No other being
has ever had the might...

62
00:06:29,127 --> 00:06:31,161
nay, the nobility...

63
00:06:31,163 --> 00:06:35,935
to wield not one,
but two Infinity Stones.

64
00:06:39,305 --> 00:06:43,841
The universe lies
within your grasp.

65
00:07:23,048 --> 00:07:25,850
There are two more stones
on Earth.

66
00:07:27,218 --> 00:07:31,053
Find them, my children,
and bring them to me on Titan.

67
00:07:31,055 --> 00:07:32,721
Father,
we will not fail you.

68
00:07:32,723 --> 00:07:35,257
If I might interject.

69
00:07:35,259 --> 00:07:39,430
If you're going to Earth,
you might want a guide.

70
00:07:39,432 --> 00:07:42,264
I do have a bit of experience
in that arena.

71
00:07:42,266 --> 00:07:44,766
If you consider
failure experience.

72
00:07:44,769 --> 00:07:47,372
I consider
experience experience.

73
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,372
Almighty Thanos...

74
00:07:50,375 --> 00:07:55,112
I, Loki, prince of Asgard...

75
00:07:58,949 --> 00:08:00,117
Odinson...

76
00:08:04,055 --> 00:08:05,990
the rightful king
of Jotunheim...

77
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:08,393
god of mischief...

78
00:08:09,293 --> 00:08:10,896
do hereby pledge to you...

79
00:08:12,230 --> 00:08:16,134
my undying fidelity.

80
00:08:26,778 --> 00:08:28,180
Undying?

81
00:08:32,018 --> 00:08:35,184
You should choose your words
more carefully.

82
00:08:56,173 --> 00:08:57,174
You...

83
00:08:58,275 --> 00:08:59,943
will never be...

84
00:09:02,514 --> 00:09:03,813
a god.

85
00:09:14,057 --> 00:09:15,058
No!

86
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:32,443
No resurrections this time.

87
00:09:56,133 --> 00:09:58,269
No. Loki.

88
00:10:37,106 --> 00:10:40,174
Seriously,
you don't have any money?

89
00:10:40,177 --> 00:10:43,345
Attachment to the material is
detachment from the spiritual.

90
00:10:43,346 --> 00:10:44,913
I'll tell the guys
at the deli.

91
00:10:44,914 --> 00:10:46,947
Maybe they'll make you
a metaphysical ham on rye.

92
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:48,950
Oh. Wait, wait, wait.
I think I have 200.

93
00:10:48,951 --> 00:10:50,085
Dollars?

94
00:10:50,086 --> 00:10:52,020
- Rupees.
- Which is?

95
00:10:52,023 --> 00:10:53,488
Uh, buck and a half.

96
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:55,356
What do you want?

97
00:10:55,359 --> 00:10:57,494
I wouldn't say no
to a tuna melt.

98
00:11:10,073 --> 00:11:12,043
Thanos is coming.

99
00:11:12,475 --> 00:11:13,875
He's coming.

100
00:11:18,014 --> 00:11:19,249
Who?

101
00:11:28,024 --> 00:11:29,390
Slow down, slow down.
I'll spell it out for you.

102
00:11:29,393 --> 00:11:30,558
You're totally rambling.

103
00:11:30,561 --> 00:11:31,493
- No, I'm not.
- You lost me.

104
00:11:31,495 --> 00:11:32,927
Look, you know how
you're having a dream,

105
00:11:32,928 --> 00:11:34,161
and in the dream
you gotta pee.

106
00:11:34,163 --> 00:11:35,297
- Yeah.
- Okay.

107
00:11:35,298 --> 00:11:36,264
And then you're like,
"Oh, my God.

108
00:11:36,265 --> 00:11:37,665
"There's no bathrooms.
What am I gonna do?

109
00:11:37,668 --> 00:11:38,932
- "Oh, someone's watching."
- Right.

110
00:11:38,934 --> 00:11:40,000
"Oh, I'm gonna
go in my pants."

111
00:11:40,003 --> 00:11:41,134
And then you wake up
and in real life

112
00:11:41,136 --> 00:11:42,235
you actually have to pee.

113
00:11:42,238 --> 00:11:43,304
- Yes.
- Yeah.

114
00:11:43,307 --> 00:11:44,538
- Okay.
- Everybody has that.

115
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:46,575
Right, that's the point
I'm trying to make.

116
00:11:46,576 --> 00:11:50,581
Apropos of that, last night
I dreamt we had a kid.

117
00:11:51,246 --> 00:11:52,713
It was so real.

118
00:11:52,716 --> 00:11:54,248
We named him
after your eccentric uncle.

119
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,383
Uh, what was his name?

120
00:11:55,384 --> 00:11:57,719
- Right.
- Morgan! Morgan.

121
00:11:57,721 --> 00:11:59,553
- So you woke up...
- Naturally.

122
00:11:59,556 --> 00:12:01,355
and thought that we were...

123
00:12:01,356 --> 00:12:02,524
- Expecting.
- Yeah.

124
00:12:02,525 --> 00:12:03,390
- Yes?
- No.

125
00:12:03,393 --> 00:12:05,225
I had a dream about it.
It was so real.

126
00:12:05,227 --> 00:12:07,227
If you wanted to have a kid...

127
00:12:07,230 --> 00:12:09,296
you wouldn't have done that.

128
00:12:09,298 --> 00:12:11,331
I'm glad you brought this up,
'cause it's nothing.

129
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:13,000
It's just a housing unit
for nanoparticles.

130
00:12:13,003 --> 00:12:14,402
You're not helping
your case, okay?

131
00:12:14,403 --> 00:12:15,636
No, this is detachable.
It's not a...

132
00:12:15,639 --> 00:12:17,471
You don't need that.

133
00:12:17,472 --> 00:12:18,606
I know, I had the surgery.

134
00:12:18,609 --> 00:12:20,008
I'm just
trying to protect us...

135
00:12:20,009 --> 00:12:21,643
and future usses
and that's it.

136
00:12:21,644 --> 00:12:23,376
Just in case there's a monster
in the closet.

137
00:12:23,379 --> 00:12:25,313
- Instead of, you know...
- Shirts.

138
00:12:27,049 --> 00:12:28,481
You know me so well.

139
00:12:28,484 --> 00:12:31,686
- God.
- You finish all my sentences.

140
00:12:31,687 --> 00:12:33,588
You should have shirts
in your closet.

141
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:35,756
Yeah.

142
00:12:35,759 --> 00:12:37,658
You know what there should be?
No more surprises.

143
00:12:37,659 --> 00:12:39,159
We're gonna have
a nice dinner tonight.

144
00:12:39,162 --> 00:12:41,294
Show off this Harry Winston.

145
00:12:41,297 --> 00:12:43,697
Right? And we should have
no more surprises. Ever.

146
00:12:43,698 --> 00:12:45,065
I should promise you.

147
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:46,302
- Yes.
- I will.

148
00:12:48,671 --> 00:12:49,769
Thank you.

149
00:12:49,772 --> 00:12:50,971
Tony Stark.

150
00:12:50,972 --> 00:12:54,243
I'm Doctor Stephen Strange.
I need you to come with me.

151
00:12:56,245 --> 00:12:59,047
Oh, uh, congratulations
on the wedding, by the way.

152
00:12:59,048 --> 00:13:01,015
I'm sorry, you giving out
tickets to something?

153
00:13:01,018 --> 00:13:03,183
We need your help.

154
00:13:03,186 --> 00:13:04,717
It's not overselling it
to say that

155
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,519
the fate of the universe
is at stake.

156
00:13:06,522 --> 00:13:08,057
And who's "we"?

157
00:13:09,625 --> 00:13:11,025
Hey, Tony.

158
00:13:11,028 --> 00:13:12,158
Bruce.

159
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,663
- Pepper.
- Hi.

160
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,366
- Oh.
- You okay?

161
00:13:20,202 --> 00:13:22,403
At the dawn
of the universe,

162
00:13:22,404 --> 00:13:24,373
there was nothing. Then...

163
00:13:24,673 --> 00:13:26,539
Boom.

164
00:13:26,542 --> 00:13:30,144
The Big Bang sent
six elemental crystals...

165
00:13:30,145 --> 00:13:33,014
hurtling across
the virgin universe.

166
00:13:34,049 --> 00:13:35,548
These Infinity Stones

167
00:13:35,551 --> 00:13:38,488
each control an essential
aspect of existence.

168
00:13:39,455 --> 00:13:40,590
Space.

169
00:13:41,691 --> 00:13:43,024
Reality.

170
00:13:44,527 --> 00:13:45,661
Power.

171
00:13:46,828 --> 00:13:48,163
Soul.

172
00:13:49,264 --> 00:13:50,399
Mind.

173
00:13:52,335 --> 00:13:53,536
And Time.

174
00:14:03,211 --> 00:14:04,477
Tell me his name again.

175
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:05,778
Thanos.

176
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:07,279
He's a plague, Tony.

177
00:14:07,282 --> 00:14:09,315
He invades planets.
He takes what he wants.

178
00:14:09,317 --> 00:14:11,552
He wipes out
half the population.

179
00:14:11,553 --> 00:14:13,821
He sent Loki.

180
00:14:13,822 --> 00:14:16,759
The attack on New York,
that's him.

181
00:14:17,424 --> 00:14:18,527
This is it.

182
00:14:19,662 --> 00:14:20,628
What's our timeline?

183
00:14:20,629 --> 00:14:23,229
No telling. He has
the Power and Space Stones.

184
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:24,163
That already makes him

185
00:14:24,164 --> 00:14:25,865
the strongest creature
in the whole universe.

186
00:14:25,868 --> 00:14:29,402
If he gets his hands
on all six stones, Tony...

187
00:14:29,403 --> 00:14:30,537
He could destroy life

188
00:14:30,538 --> 00:14:32,706
on a scale
hitherto undreamt of.

189
00:14:32,707 --> 00:14:34,707
Did you seriously just say
"hitherto undreamt of"?

190
00:14:34,710 --> 00:14:36,876
Are you seriously leaning
on the Cauldron of the Cosmos?

191
00:14:36,879 --> 00:14:38,513
Is that what it is?

192
00:14:41,283 --> 00:14:43,217
I'm going to allow that.

193
00:14:45,386 --> 00:14:46,820
If Thanos needs all six,
why don't we just

194
00:14:46,822 --> 00:14:48,453
stick this one down
a garbage disposal?

195
00:14:48,456 --> 00:14:49,688
No can do.

196
00:14:49,691 --> 00:14:52,491
We swore an oath to protect
the Time Stone with our lives.

197
00:14:52,494 --> 00:14:53,759
And I swore off dairy...

198
00:14:53,761 --> 00:14:56,395
but then Ben & Jerry's named
a flavor after me.

199
00:14:56,398 --> 00:14:57,898
- Stark Raving Hazelnuts.
- Not bad.

200
00:14:57,899 --> 00:14:59,532
A bit chalky.

201
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:01,301
A Hunk of Hulk of
Burning Fudge is our favorite.

202
00:15:01,302 --> 00:15:02,467
- That's a thing?
- Whatever.

203
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:03,570
Point is, things change.

204
00:15:03,572 --> 00:15:06,673
Our oath to protect
the Time Stone cannot change.

205
00:15:06,674 --> 00:15:08,841
And this stone may be the best
chance we have against Thanos.

206
00:15:08,842 --> 00:15:09,741
Yeah, so conversely,

207
00:15:09,744 --> 00:15:11,878
it may also be
his best chance against us.

208
00:15:11,879 --> 00:15:13,513
Well, if we don't do our jobs.

209
00:15:13,514 --> 00:15:14,581
What is your job exactly?

210
00:15:14,582 --> 00:15:16,283
Besides making
balloon animals.

211
00:15:17,384 --> 00:15:20,153
Protecting your reality,
douchebag.

212
00:15:20,154 --> 00:15:22,688
Okay, guys. Could we table
this discussion right now?

213
00:15:22,691 --> 00:15:24,657
The fact is
we have this stone.

214
00:15:24,658 --> 00:15:26,392
We know where it is.

215
00:15:26,394 --> 00:15:28,794
Vision is out there somewhere
with the Mind Stone...

216
00:15:28,797 --> 00:15:30,565
and we have to find him now.

217
00:15:31,399 --> 00:15:32,798
Yeah, that's the thing.

218
00:15:32,801 --> 00:15:33,799
What do you mean?

219
00:15:33,802 --> 00:15:36,336
Two weeks ago, Vision turned
off his transponder.

220
00:15:36,337 --> 00:15:37,503
He's offline.

221
00:15:37,504 --> 00:15:38,837
- What?
- Yeah.

222
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,907
Tony, you lost
another super-bot?

223
00:15:40,908 --> 00:15:43,442
I didn't lose him. He's more
than that. He's evolving.

224
00:15:43,445 --> 00:15:44,812
Who could find Vision then?

225
00:15:47,816 --> 00:15:49,548
Shit.

226
00:15:49,551 --> 00:15:50,682
Probably Steve Rogers.

227
00:15:50,684 --> 00:15:51,820
Oh, great.

228
00:15:52,386 --> 00:15:53,554
Maybe.

229
00:15:54,254 --> 00:15:55,254
But...

230
00:15:58,626 --> 00:15:59,727
Call him.

231
00:16:00,528 --> 00:16:02,828
It's not that easy.

232
00:16:02,831 --> 00:16:04,797
God, we haven't caught up
in a spell, have we?

233
00:16:04,798 --> 00:16:05,865
No.

234
00:16:05,866 --> 00:16:07,601
The Avengers broke up.
We're toast.

235
00:16:08,302 --> 00:16:09,370
Broke up?

236
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:13,337
Like a band?
Like... Like the Beatles?

237
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:15,274
Cap and I fell out hard.

238
00:16:16,275 --> 00:16:17,411
We're not on speaking terms.

239
00:16:18,779 --> 00:16:21,381
Tony, listen to me.

240
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:23,717
Thor's gone.

241
00:16:25,485 --> 00:16:26,518
Thanos is coming.

242
00:16:26,519 --> 00:16:28,389
It doesn't matter
who you're talking to or not.

243
00:16:45,605 --> 00:16:46,606
Flip phone.

244
00:17:07,694 --> 00:17:08,928
Say, Doc, you wouldn't
happen to be

245
00:17:08,930 --> 00:17:10,263
moving your hair, would ya?

246
00:17:11,032 --> 00:17:13,464
Not at the moment, no.

247
00:17:45,965 --> 00:17:47,835
You okay?

248
00:17:48,935 --> 00:17:50,067
- Help him!
- Banner!

249
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,869
- Wong! Look alive!
- Go, go! We got it!

250
00:17:51,872 --> 00:17:52,938
Friday, what am I looking at?

251
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:54,573
Not sure.
I'm working on it.

252
00:17:54,575 --> 00:17:56,674
Hey! You might wanna
put that Time Stone

253
00:17:56,676 --> 00:17:57,976
in your back pocket, Doc!

254
00:17:57,978 --> 00:17:59,346
Might wanna use it.

255
00:18:26,707 --> 00:18:29,074
Ned, hey. I need you
to cause a distraction.

256
00:18:29,076 --> 00:18:30,808
Holy shit.

257
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:32,509
We're all gonna die!

258
00:18:32,511 --> 00:18:33,811
There's a spaceship!

259
00:18:33,814 --> 00:18:35,646
- What's going on?
- Oh, my God!

260
00:18:44,025 --> 00:18:45,355
What's the matter
with you kids?

261
00:18:45,357 --> 00:18:46,993
You never seen
a spaceship before?

262
00:18:59,404 --> 00:19:01,739
Friday, evac anyone
south of 43rd Street.

263
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:02,874
Notify first responders.

264
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:04,011
Will do.

265
00:19:32,505 --> 00:19:35,441
Hear me and rejoice.

266
00:19:36,741 --> 00:19:38,175
You are about to die

267
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:40,477
at the hands
of the Children of Thanos.

268
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:43,048
Be thankful...

269
00:19:43,049 --> 00:19:45,982
that your meaningless lives
are now contributing...

270
00:19:45,984 --> 00:19:48,919
I'm sorry,
Earth is closed today.

271
00:19:48,921 --> 00:19:51,822
You better pack it up
and get outta here.

272
00:19:51,824 --> 00:19:53,891
Stonekeeper.

273
00:19:53,893 --> 00:19:56,426
Does this chattering animal
speak for you?

274
00:19:56,429 --> 00:19:58,628
Certainly not.
I speak for myself.

275
00:19:58,631 --> 00:20:00,967
You're trespassing in
this city and on this planet.

276
00:20:01,968 --> 00:20:03,666
He means get lost, Squidward.

277
00:20:03,669 --> 00:20:04,868
He exhausts me.

278
00:20:04,871 --> 00:20:06,971
Bring me the stone.

279
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:09,976
Banner, you want a piece?

280
00:20:10,675 --> 00:20:12,542
Mmm, no, not really.

281
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:13,911
But when do I ever get
what I want?

282
00:20:13,913 --> 00:20:14,913
That's right.

283
00:20:15,681 --> 00:20:16,980
Okay. Push!

284
00:20:16,982 --> 00:20:18,682
It's been a while.

285
00:20:18,683 --> 00:20:20,217
It's gonna be good
to have you, buddy.

286
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:21,384
Okay. Shh.

287
00:20:21,385 --> 00:20:24,221
Let me just... I need to
concentrate here for a second.

288
00:20:24,222 --> 00:20:25,722
Come on, come on, man.

289
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,926
God!

290
00:20:29,028 --> 00:20:30,492
Where's your guy?

291
00:20:31,763 --> 00:20:33,197
I don't know. We've sorta
been having a thing.

292
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:34,565
- It's no time for a thing.
- I know.

293
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:36,086
That's the thing right there.
Let's go.

294
00:20:43,108 --> 00:20:44,307
Dude, you're embarrassing me
in front of the wizards.

295
00:20:44,309 --> 00:20:46,576
Tony, I'm sorry.
Either I can't or he won't.

296
00:20:46,577 --> 00:20:47,542
It's okay.

297
00:20:47,545 --> 00:20:50,079
Hey, stand down.
Keep an eye on him. Thank you.

298
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:51,548
- I have him.
- Damn it.

299
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:20,576
Where'd that come from?

300
00:21:20,577 --> 00:21:21,644
It's nanotech.

301
00:21:21,645 --> 00:21:23,046
You like it?
A little something I...

302
00:21:26,518 --> 00:21:28,817
Doctor Banner, if the rest
of your green friend

303
00:21:28,819 --> 00:21:30,020
won't be joining us...

304
00:21:39,663 --> 00:21:41,030
Gotta get that stone
outta here, now.

305
00:21:41,032 --> 00:21:42,531
It stays with me.

306
00:21:42,534 --> 00:21:43,535
Exactly. Bye.

307
00:21:53,144 --> 00:21:54,644
Tony, you okay?

308
00:21:54,645 --> 00:21:56,679
- How we doing? Good? Bad?
- Really, really good.

309
00:21:56,681 --> 00:21:57,913
Really good.
Do you plan on helping out?

310
00:21:57,915 --> 00:21:59,150
I'm trying. He won't come out.

311
00:22:01,051 --> 00:22:02,119
Hammer.

312
00:22:09,928 --> 00:22:12,961
Come on, Hulk!
What are you doing to me?

313
00:22:12,963 --> 00:22:15,198
Come out! Come out! Come out!

314
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,568
No!

315
00:22:21,271 --> 00:22:23,107
What do you mean, "no"?

316
00:22:28,913 --> 00:22:30,747
Hey, man.
What's up, Mr. Stark?

317
00:22:30,749 --> 00:22:33,585
- Kid, where'd you come from?
- A field trip to MoMA.

318
00:22:35,619 --> 00:22:37,259
Uh, what is this guy's
problem, Mr. Stark?

319
00:22:37,922 --> 00:22:38,988
Uh, he's from space.

320
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:41,223
He came here to steal
a necklace from a wizard.

321
00:23:07,885 --> 00:23:09,818
Your powers are quaint.

322
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:11,622
You must be popular
with children.

323
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:16,358
It's a simple spell
but quite unbreakable.

324
00:23:16,361 --> 00:23:18,794
Then I'll take it
off your corpse.

325
00:23:31,375 --> 00:23:36,778
You'll find removing a
dead man's spell troublesome.

326
00:23:36,779 --> 00:23:38,413
You'll only wish
you were dead.

327
00:23:48,724 --> 00:23:49,726
No!

328
00:23:53,864 --> 00:23:55,397
Kid,
that's the wizard. Get on it.

329
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,035
On it!

330
00:24:04,375 --> 00:24:05,875
Not cool.

331
00:24:10,079 --> 00:24:11,080
Gotcha!

332
00:24:12,249 --> 00:24:13,250
Wait!

333
00:24:21,224 --> 00:24:24,092
Uh, Mr. Stark,
I'm being beamed up.

334
00:24:24,094 --> 00:24:25,328
Hang on, kid.

335
00:24:41,077 --> 00:24:42,378
Oh!

336
00:24:44,213 --> 00:24:45,279
Ugh.

337
00:24:45,281 --> 00:24:47,084
Wong, you're invited
to my wedding.

338
00:24:54,724 --> 00:24:55,924
Give me a little juice,
Friday.

339
00:25:04,768 --> 00:25:06,167
Unlock 17:A.

340
00:25:19,115 --> 00:25:20,949
Pete, you gotta let go.
I'm gonna catch you.

341
00:25:20,951 --> 00:25:23,317
But you said
save the wizard!

342
00:25:23,319 --> 00:25:24,419
I can't breathe.

343
00:25:25,422 --> 00:25:27,290
We're too high up.
You're running out of air.

344
00:25:28,258 --> 00:25:30,460
Yeah. That makes sense.

345
00:25:47,809 --> 00:25:49,943
Mr. Stark, it smells
like a new car in here!

346
00:25:49,945 --> 00:25:50,944
Happy trails, kid.

347
00:25:50,947 --> 00:25:52,468
- Friday, send him home.
- Yep.

348
00:25:53,349 --> 00:25:54,916
Oh, come on!

349
00:26:03,259 --> 00:26:05,393
Boss, incoming call
from Miss Potts.

350
00:26:05,394 --> 00:26:06,428
Tony? Oh, my God.

351
00:26:06,430 --> 00:26:07,494
Are you all right?
What's going on?

352
00:26:07,497 --> 00:26:08,563
Yeah, I'm fine.
I just think

353
00:26:08,565 --> 00:26:10,397
we might have to push
our 8:30 res.

354
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,532
Why?

355
00:26:11,535 --> 00:26:13,200
Just 'cause
I'll probably

356
00:26:13,201 --> 00:26:15,803
not make it back for a while.

357
00:26:15,805 --> 00:26:17,070
Tell me
you're not on that ship.

358
00:26:17,073 --> 00:26:18,339
Yeah.

359
00:26:18,342 --> 00:26:19,540
God, no, please tell me
you're not on the ship.

360
00:26:19,542 --> 00:26:21,343
Honey, I'm sorry.

361
00:26:21,345 --> 00:26:22,376
I'm sorry,
I don't know what to say.

362
00:26:22,378 --> 00:26:24,077
Come back here, Tony.
I swear to God.

363
00:26:24,079 --> 00:26:26,247
- Pep.
- Come back here right now.

364
00:26:26,249 --> 00:26:27,280
Come back.

365
00:26:27,282 --> 00:26:30,049
Boss,
we're losing her.

366
00:26:30,051 --> 00:26:31,488
I'm going too.

367
00:26:40,564 --> 00:26:41,963
Oh, my God!

368
00:26:46,335 --> 00:26:48,304
I shoulda stayed on the bus.

369
00:27:02,585 --> 00:27:04,317
Where you going?

370
00:27:04,319 --> 00:27:05,952
The Time Stone's been taken.

371
00:27:05,954 --> 00:27:07,890
The Sanctum remains unguarded.

372
00:27:08,391 --> 00:27:09,959
What will you do?

373
00:27:10,593 --> 00:27:12,327
I'm gonna make a call.

374
00:27:52,567 --> 00:27:53,902
Sing it, Drax!

375
00:28:06,382 --> 00:28:08,015
Why are we doing this again?

376
00:28:08,017 --> 00:28:09,583
It's a distress signal,
Rocket.

377
00:28:09,585 --> 00:28:10,916
Someone could be dying.

378
00:28:10,919 --> 00:28:13,118
I get that,
but why are we doing it?

379
00:28:13,121 --> 00:28:15,087
'Cause we're nice.

380
00:28:15,089 --> 00:28:16,154
And maybe whoever it is

381
00:28:16,156 --> 00:28:18,025
will give us a little
cheddar cheese for our effort.

382
00:28:18,027 --> 00:28:20,426
- Which isn't the point.
- Which isn't the point.

383
00:28:20,429 --> 00:28:22,328
I mean,
if he doesn't pony up...

384
00:28:22,330 --> 00:28:23,497
We take his ship.

385
00:28:23,499 --> 00:28:25,298
- Exactly!
- Bingo!

386
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:26,301
All right!

387
00:28:29,538 --> 00:28:31,438
We are arriving.

388
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:32,506
All right, Guardians,

389
00:28:32,508 --> 00:28:33,940
don't forget
this might be dangerous...

390
00:28:33,942 --> 00:28:36,176
so let's put on
our mean faces.

391
00:28:41,383 --> 00:28:43,082
Groot, put that
thing away, now.

392
00:28:43,084 --> 00:28:44,150
I don't wanna tell you again.

393
00:28:44,152 --> 00:28:45,384
Groot.

394
00:28:45,386 --> 00:28:46,552
I am Groot!

395
00:28:46,555 --> 00:28:47,653
- Whoa!
- Language!

396
00:28:47,655 --> 00:28:49,255
- Hey!
- Wow.

397
00:28:49,257 --> 00:28:51,124
You got some
acorns on you, kid.

398
00:28:51,125 --> 00:28:52,625
Ever since
you got a little sap,

399
00:28:52,627 --> 00:28:54,595
you're a total d-hole.

400
00:28:54,596 --> 00:28:57,999
Now, keep it up, and I'm gonna
smash that thing to pieces.

401
00:29:04,740 --> 00:29:06,374
What happened?

402
00:29:10,412 --> 00:29:11,680
Oh, my God.

403
00:29:17,352 --> 00:29:19,153
Looks like
we're not getting paid.

404
00:29:21,355 --> 00:29:23,455
Wipers! Wipers!

405
00:29:23,458 --> 00:29:24,692
Get it off.

406
00:29:31,432 --> 00:29:34,366
How the hell
is this dude still alive?

407
00:29:34,368 --> 00:29:36,335
He is not a dude.

408
00:29:36,336 --> 00:29:38,237
You're a dude.

409
00:29:38,239 --> 00:29:41,574
This... This is a man.

410
00:29:41,576 --> 00:29:44,509
A handsome, muscular man.

411
00:29:44,511 --> 00:29:45,577
I'm muscular.

412
00:29:45,579 --> 00:29:46,645
But who are you
kidding, Quill?

413
00:29:46,647 --> 00:29:48,213
You're one sandwich
away from fat.

414
00:29:48,215 --> 00:29:49,214
Yeah, right.

415
00:29:49,217 --> 00:29:50,750
It's true, Quill.
You have put on weight.

416
00:29:50,751 --> 00:29:51,951
What?

417
00:29:54,189 --> 00:29:56,057
Gamora, do you think I'm...

418
00:29:58,292 --> 00:30:02,094
He is anxious, angry.

419
00:30:02,096 --> 00:30:05,698
He feels
tremendous loss and guilt.

420
00:30:05,700 --> 00:30:08,567
It's like a pirate had a baby
with an angel.

421
00:30:08,569 --> 00:30:09,535
Wow.

422
00:30:09,537 --> 00:30:11,737
This is a real wake-up call
for me. Okay.

423
00:30:11,739 --> 00:30:14,640
I'm gonna get a Bowflex.
I'm gonna commit.

424
00:30:14,642 --> 00:30:15,708
I'm gonna get some dumbbells.

425
00:30:15,710 --> 00:30:17,343
You know you can't
eat dumbbells, right?

426
00:30:17,345 --> 00:30:18,577
It's like his muscles

427
00:30:18,579 --> 00:30:20,645
are made
of Cotati metal fibers.

428
00:30:20,647 --> 00:30:22,416
Stop massaging his muscles.

429
00:30:24,251 --> 00:30:25,252
Wake him up.

430
00:30:28,323 --> 00:30:29,588
Wake.

431
00:30:46,807 --> 00:30:49,209
Who the hell are you guys?

432
00:30:51,846 --> 00:30:55,681
The entire time I knew Thanos,
he only ever had one goal.

433
00:30:55,682 --> 00:30:57,517
To bring balance
to the universe

434
00:30:57,519 --> 00:31:00,586
by wiping out
half of all life.

435
00:31:00,587 --> 00:31:02,821
He used to kill people
planet by planet,

436
00:31:02,824 --> 00:31:04,556
massacre by massacre.

437
00:31:04,557 --> 00:31:06,191
Including my own.

438
00:31:06,192 --> 00:31:07,792
If he gets
all six Infinity Stones...

439
00:31:07,795 --> 00:31:11,162
he can do it with the snap
of his fingers like this.

440
00:31:11,163 --> 00:31:13,766
You seem to know
a great deal about Thanos.

441
00:31:13,768 --> 00:31:17,604
Gamora
is the daughter of Thanos.

442
00:31:21,642 --> 00:31:23,710
Your father killed my brother.

443
00:31:24,176 --> 00:31:25,477
Oh, boy.

444
00:31:25,479 --> 00:31:27,345
Stepfather, technically.

445
00:31:27,346 --> 00:31:29,282
And she hates him
as much as you do.

446
00:31:32,854 --> 00:31:34,618
Families can be tough.

447
00:31:34,621 --> 00:31:36,153
Before my father died,

448
00:31:36,155 --> 00:31:37,890
he told me
that I had a half-sister...

449
00:31:37,892 --> 00:31:40,424
that he imprisoned in Hel.

450
00:31:40,426 --> 00:31:43,528
And then she returned home
and stabbed me in the eye.

451
00:31:43,529 --> 00:31:44,896
So I had to kill her.

452
00:31:44,898 --> 00:31:47,198
That's life though,
isn't it, I guess.

453
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,402
Goes round and round and...

454
00:31:49,269 --> 00:31:50,402
I feel your pain.

455
00:31:50,403 --> 00:31:52,770
I feel your pain as well,
because...

456
00:31:52,772 --> 00:31:54,172
I mean,
it's not a competition,

457
00:31:54,173 --> 00:31:55,406
but I've been through a lot.

458
00:31:55,409 --> 00:31:57,275
My father killed my mother.

459
00:31:57,277 --> 00:31:58,442
And then I had to kill
my father.

460
00:31:58,444 --> 00:32:00,178
That was hard.

461
00:32:00,180 --> 00:32:03,515
Probably even harder
than having to kill a sister.

462
00:32:03,517 --> 00:32:06,550
Plus, I came out with
both my eyes, which was...

463
00:32:06,553 --> 00:32:08,321
I need a hammer, not a spoon.

464
00:32:10,190 --> 00:32:13,692
How do I open this thing?
Is there some sort of, uh...

465
00:32:13,693 --> 00:32:16,394
A four-digit code, maybe?
Maybe a birthdate.

466
00:32:16,395 --> 00:32:19,763
- Uh, what are you doing?
- Taking your pod.

467
00:32:21,268 --> 00:32:22,469
No, you're not.

468
00:32:24,403 --> 00:32:28,707
You will not be taking
our pod today, sir.

469
00:32:28,709 --> 00:32:32,211
Uh... Quill, are you making
your voice deeper?

470
00:32:33,947 --> 00:32:35,779
- No.
- You are.

471
00:32:35,781 --> 00:32:38,682
You're imitating the god-man.
It's weird.

472
00:32:38,684 --> 00:32:40,183
No, I'm not.

473
00:32:40,185 --> 00:32:42,188
- He just did it again!
- This is my voice.

474
00:32:48,326 --> 00:32:49,693
Are you mocking me?

475
00:32:49,695 --> 00:32:53,230
- Are you mocking me?
- Stop it. You did it again.

476
00:32:53,231 --> 00:32:54,298
He's trying to copy me.

477
00:32:54,299 --> 00:32:55,432
I need you to stop doing that.

478
00:32:55,433 --> 00:32:57,267
- Enough!
- He's doing it first.

479
00:32:57,269 --> 00:32:58,702
We need to stop Thanos.

480
00:32:58,704 --> 00:33:00,403
Which means
we need to find out

481
00:33:00,405 --> 00:33:01,538
where he's going next.

482
00:33:01,540 --> 00:33:02,874
Knowhere.

483
00:33:02,875 --> 00:33:04,742
He must be going somewhere.

484
00:33:04,744 --> 00:33:06,877
No, no. Knowhere?

485
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:09,748
It's a place.
We've been there. It sucks.

486
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:12,616
- Excuse me, that's our food.
- Not anymore.

487
00:33:12,618 --> 00:33:15,886
Thor, why would he
go to Knowhere?

488
00:33:15,888 --> 00:33:17,354
Because for years...

489
00:33:17,355 --> 00:33:19,556
the Reality Stone's been
safely stored there

490
00:33:19,557 --> 00:33:21,224
with a man
called the Collector.

491
00:33:21,227 --> 00:33:22,826
If it's with the
Collector, then it's not safe.

492
00:33:22,828 --> 00:33:24,729
Only an idiot
would give that man a stone.

493
00:33:24,730 --> 00:33:26,363
- Or a genius.
- How do you know...

494
00:33:26,365 --> 00:33:28,932
he's not going
for one of the other stones?

495
00:33:28,934 --> 00:33:31,567
There are six stones
out there.

496
00:33:31,569 --> 00:33:33,872
Thanos already has
the Power Stone...

497
00:33:33,874 --> 00:33:37,674
because he stole it last week
when he decimated Xandar.

498
00:33:37,676 --> 00:33:39,844
He stole the Space Stone
from me...

499
00:33:39,846 --> 00:33:42,712
when he destroyed my ship and
slaughtered half my people.

500
00:33:42,714 --> 00:33:44,480
The Time and Mind Stones
are safe on Earth.

501
00:33:44,482 --> 00:33:45,749
They're with the Avengers.

502
00:33:45,750 --> 00:33:48,285
- The Avengers?
- Earth's mightiest heroes.

503
00:33:48,287 --> 00:33:49,519
Like Kevin Bacon?

504
00:33:49,521 --> 00:33:50,820
He may be on the team.
I don't know.

505
00:33:50,823 --> 00:33:51,888
I haven't been there
in a while.

506
00:33:51,891 --> 00:33:54,458
As for the Soul Stone, well,
no one's ever seen that.

507
00:33:54,460 --> 00:33:56,292
No one even knows where it is.

508
00:33:56,295 --> 00:33:57,961
Therefore Thanos can't get it.

509
00:33:57,963 --> 00:33:59,663
Therefore he's going
to Knowhere.

510
00:33:59,664 --> 00:34:02,332
Hence he'll be getting
the Reality Stone.

511
00:34:02,334 --> 00:34:03,500
You're welcome.

512
00:34:03,501 --> 00:34:04,801
Then we have to go
to Knowhere now.

513
00:34:04,804 --> 00:34:08,905
Wrong. Where we have to go
is Nidavellir.

514
00:34:08,907 --> 00:34:10,907
- That's a made-up word.
- All words are made up.

515
00:34:10,909 --> 00:34:14,311
Nidavellir is real? Seriously?

516
00:34:14,313 --> 00:34:15,945
That place is a legend.

517
00:34:15,947 --> 00:34:17,547
They make the most powerful,
horrific weapons

518
00:34:17,550 --> 00:34:19,717
to ever torment the universe.

519
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:21,885
I would very much like
to go there, please.

520
00:34:21,887 --> 00:34:22,952
The rabbit is correct

521
00:34:22,954 --> 00:34:24,054
and clearly the smartest
among you.

522
00:34:24,056 --> 00:34:25,088
Rabbit?

523
00:34:25,090 --> 00:34:27,757
Only Eitri the Dwarf can
make me the weapon I need.

524
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,059
I assume
you're the captain, sir.

525
00:34:29,061 --> 00:34:30,393
You're very perceptive.

526
00:34:30,396 --> 00:34:31,628
You seem like a noble leader.

527
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:33,429
Will you join me
on my quest to Nidavellir?

528
00:34:33,431 --> 00:34:36,400
Let me just ask the captain.
Oh, wait a second, it's me!

529
00:34:36,402 --> 00:34:38,335
- Yeah. I'll go.
- Wonderful!

530
00:34:38,336 --> 00:34:39,503
Uh, except for that
I'm the captain.

531
00:34:39,505 --> 00:34:40,704
Quiet.

532
00:34:40,706 --> 00:34:42,371
- That's my backpack.
- Go sit down.

533
00:34:42,373 --> 00:34:44,007
Look, this is my ship.

534
00:34:44,010 --> 00:34:46,809
And I'm not goin' to...

535
00:34:46,811 --> 00:34:49,012
Wait, what kinda weapon
are we talkin' about here?

536
00:34:49,014 --> 00:34:51,081
The Thanos-killing kind.

537
00:34:51,083 --> 00:34:52,815
Don't you think that we should
all have a weapon like that?

538
00:34:52,818 --> 00:34:54,985
No. You simply lack
the strength to wield them.

539
00:34:54,987 --> 00:34:56,318
Your bodies would crumble

540
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,588
as your minds collapsed
into madness.

541
00:34:57,590 --> 00:34:59,655
Is it weird that I wanna do it
even more now?

542
00:34:59,657 --> 00:35:00,923
Mmm, a little bit, yeah.

543
00:35:00,925 --> 00:35:02,391
If we don't go to Knowhere

544
00:35:02,393 --> 00:35:03,994
and Thanos retrieves
another stone...

545
00:35:03,996 --> 00:35:05,762
he'll be too powerful to stop.

546
00:35:05,764 --> 00:35:08,032
- He already is.
- I got it figured out.

547
00:35:08,034 --> 00:35:09,867
We got two ships

548
00:35:09,869 --> 00:35:11,501
and a large assortment
of morons.

549
00:35:11,503 --> 00:35:14,838
So me and Groot will go
with the pirate angel here.

550
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:16,039
And the morons
will go to Knowhere

551
00:35:16,041 --> 00:35:17,840
to try to stop Thanos.

552
00:35:17,842 --> 00:35:19,909
- Cool? Cool.
- So cool.

553
00:35:19,911 --> 00:35:21,945
For the record...

554
00:35:21,947 --> 00:35:23,478
I know that
you're going with him

555
00:35:23,481 --> 00:35:24,681
because it's where
Thanos isn't.

556
00:35:24,682 --> 00:35:26,349
You know, you really shouldn't

557
00:35:26,351 --> 00:35:28,452
talk that way
to your captain, Quill.

558
00:35:29,420 --> 00:35:31,121
Come on, Groot.

559
00:35:31,123 --> 00:35:33,956
Put that game down.
You'll rot your brain.

560
00:35:37,661 --> 00:35:40,663
I bid you farewell
and good luck, morons.

561
00:35:40,664 --> 00:35:41,766
Bye.

562
00:35:56,581 --> 00:35:58,048
Vis?

563
00:35:58,050 --> 00:36:00,117
Is it the stone again?

564
00:36:00,119 --> 00:36:01,820
It's as if
it's speaking to me.

565
00:36:02,519 --> 00:36:05,023
What does it say?

566
00:36:05,025 --> 00:36:07,492
I don't... I don't know,
but something.

567
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:10,862
Hey.

568
00:36:20,737 --> 00:36:23,340
Tell me what you feel.

569
00:36:30,148 --> 00:36:32,916
I just feel you.

570
00:36:41,059 --> 00:36:43,125
So there's a 10:00 a.m.
to Glasgow...

571
00:36:43,126 --> 00:36:45,460
which would give us more time
together before you went back.

572
00:36:45,463 --> 00:36:46,963
What if
I miss that train?

573
00:36:46,965 --> 00:36:48,097
There's an 11:00.

574
00:36:48,099 --> 00:36:50,635
What if I missed
all the trains?

575
00:36:51,936 --> 00:36:53,835
What if this time
I didn't go back?

576
00:36:53,838 --> 00:36:55,438
But you gave Stark your word.

577
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:56,606
I'd rather give it to you.

578
00:36:56,608 --> 00:36:58,807
Well, there are people who are
expecting me too, you know.

579
00:36:58,809 --> 00:37:00,208
We both made promises.

580
00:37:00,210 --> 00:37:01,980
Not to each other.

581
00:37:02,512 --> 00:37:04,480
Wanda.

582
00:37:04,481 --> 00:37:06,882
For two years,
we've stolen these moments...

583
00:37:06,885 --> 00:37:09,050
trying to see
if this could work and...

584
00:37:09,052 --> 00:37:10,853
I don't know.

585
00:37:10,855 --> 00:37:12,889
You know what, I'm just
gonna speak for myself.

586
00:37:12,891 --> 00:37:14,856
I think...

587
00:37:14,858 --> 00:37:16,057
- It works.
- It works.

588
00:37:16,059 --> 00:37:17,494
It works.

589
00:37:19,864 --> 00:37:21,065
Stay.

590
00:37:22,001 --> 00:37:23,735
Stay with me.

591
00:37:28,538 --> 00:37:31,742
Or not. If I'm overstepping...

592
00:37:38,782 --> 00:37:40,849
What are they?

593
00:37:40,851 --> 00:37:43,186
What the stone
was warning me about.

594
00:37:53,164 --> 00:37:54,695
I have to go.

595
00:37:54,697 --> 00:37:56,197
No, Vision.

596
00:37:56,199 --> 00:37:57,666
Vision, if that's true,

597
00:37:57,668 --> 00:38:00,503
then maybe
going isn't the best idea.

598
00:38:01,538 --> 00:38:02,737
Wanda, I...

599
00:38:02,739 --> 00:38:04,775
Vision!

600
00:38:32,902 --> 00:38:36,570
The blade,
it stopped me from phasing.

601
00:38:36,572 --> 00:38:38,574
- Is that even possible?
- It isn't supposed to be.

602
00:38:39,608 --> 00:38:42,110
My systems are failing.

603
00:38:42,112 --> 00:38:44,847
I'm beginning to think
we should have stayed in bed.

604
00:38:47,284 --> 00:38:48,485
Vis!

605
00:38:57,561 --> 00:39:00,929
Give up the stone,
and she lives.

606
00:39:38,969 --> 00:39:40,137
Hands off.

607
00:39:55,985 --> 00:39:57,318
Come on. Come on.

608
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:59,286
Come on, you gotta get up.

609
00:39:59,289 --> 00:40:01,657
You gotta get up.
Come on. Hey.

610
00:40:02,724 --> 00:40:04,358
Hey. We have to go.

611
00:40:05,996 --> 00:40:08,762
Please. Please leave.

612
00:40:08,764 --> 00:40:10,599
You asked me to stay.

613
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:12,934
- I'm staying.
- Please.

614
00:41:24,106 --> 00:41:26,007
- Get up.
- I can't.

615
00:41:26,009 --> 00:41:28,909
We don't wanna kill you,
but we will.

616
00:41:28,911 --> 00:41:31,047
You'll never get
the chance again.

617
00:41:47,030 --> 00:41:48,929
Can you stand?

618
00:41:53,268 --> 00:41:54,802
Thank you, Captain.

619
00:41:57,373 --> 00:41:59,074
Let's get you on the jet.

620
00:42:03,045 --> 00:42:06,512
Now, I thought we had a deal.

621
00:42:06,514 --> 00:42:10,416
Stay close, check in,
don't take any chances.

622
00:42:10,418 --> 00:42:12,019
I'm sorry.

623
00:42:12,021 --> 00:42:13,855
We just wanted time.

624
00:42:16,425 --> 00:42:17,824
Where to, Cap?

625
00:42:20,496 --> 00:42:22,097
Home.

626
00:42:25,766 --> 00:42:27,867
We'll be safe.
We'll be safe.

627
00:42:52,260 --> 00:42:53,427
Zehobereians.

628
00:42:53,429 --> 00:42:55,362
Mother! Where's my mother?

629
00:42:55,364 --> 00:42:56,963
Choose a side or die.

630
00:42:56,965 --> 00:42:58,465
Mother!

631
00:42:58,467 --> 00:43:00,932
One side
is a revelation...

632
00:43:00,934 --> 00:43:03,972
the other an honor
known only to a few.

633
00:43:04,905 --> 00:43:06,972
What's wrong, little one?

634
00:43:06,974 --> 00:43:10,311
My mother. Where is my mother?

635
00:43:15,148 --> 00:43:16,317
What's your name?

636
00:43:17,585 --> 00:43:19,918
Gamora.

637
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:22,023
You're quite the fighter,
Gamora.

638
00:43:23,458 --> 00:43:24,956
Come.

639
00:43:24,958 --> 00:43:25,960
Let me help you.

640
00:43:39,373 --> 00:43:40,474
Look.

641
00:43:44,211 --> 00:43:46,545
Pretty, isn't it?

642
00:43:46,547 --> 00:43:50,248
Perfectly balanced,
as all things should be.

643
00:43:50,251 --> 00:43:54,054
Too much to one side
or the other...

644
00:43:58,059 --> 00:44:00,927
Here. You try.

645
00:44:04,532 --> 00:44:07,800
Now, go in peace
to meet your maker.

646
00:44:09,202 --> 00:44:11,072
Uh-uh.

647
00:44:13,007 --> 00:44:14,507
Concentrate.

648
00:44:17,411 --> 00:44:20,248
There. You've got it.

649
00:44:29,657 --> 00:44:30,923
Gamora.

650
00:44:31,992 --> 00:44:33,059
Do you know if these grenades

651
00:44:33,061 --> 00:44:35,393
are the blow-off-your-junk
kind or the gas kind?

652
00:44:35,396 --> 00:44:36,528
Because I was thinking about

653
00:44:36,530 --> 00:44:38,264
hanging a couple
on my belt right here.

654
00:44:38,266 --> 00:44:39,398
But I don't want to
if they're the...

655
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:40,601
I need to ask a favor.

656
00:44:41,536 --> 00:44:43,003
Yeah, sure.

657
00:44:44,438 --> 00:44:45,570
One way or another,

658
00:44:45,572 --> 00:44:47,974
the path that we're on
leads to Thanos.

659
00:44:49,577 --> 00:44:52,110
Which is what
the grenades are for.

660
00:44:52,112 --> 00:44:54,382
Uh, I'm sorry.
What's the favor?

661
00:44:56,650 --> 00:44:57,851
If things go wrong...

662
00:44:59,353 --> 00:45:01,456
If Thanos gets me...

663
00:45:06,092 --> 00:45:08,061
I want you to promise me...

664
00:45:09,096 --> 00:45:10,197
you'll kill me.

665
00:45:10,996 --> 00:45:11,998
What?

666
00:45:15,135 --> 00:45:17,438
I know something he doesn't.

667
00:45:20,072 --> 00:45:22,306
And if he finds it out,

668
00:45:22,309 --> 00:45:23,748
the entire universe
could be at risk.

669
00:45:24,344 --> 00:45:25,543
What do you know?

670
00:45:25,545 --> 00:45:27,581
If I tell you, you'd know too.

671
00:45:30,617 --> 00:45:32,550
If it's so important...

672
00:45:32,552 --> 00:45:33,719
shouldn't I?

673
00:45:33,721 --> 00:45:34,885
Only if you wanna die.

674
00:45:34,887 --> 00:45:37,007
Why does somebody always
have to die in this scenario?

675
00:45:38,224 --> 00:45:39,226
Just...

676
00:45:41,561 --> 00:45:44,697
Trust me.
And possibly kill me.

677
00:45:44,699 --> 00:45:47,297
I mean, I'd like to.

678
00:45:47,300 --> 00:45:49,300
I really would. But you...

679
00:45:49,302 --> 00:45:50,469
Swear to me.

680
00:45:54,074 --> 00:45:56,309
Swear to me on your mother.

681
00:46:03,315 --> 00:46:04,317
Okay.

682
00:46:10,389 --> 00:46:11,490
Okay.

683
00:46:27,673 --> 00:46:28,773
- Oh.
- Dude.

684
00:46:28,775 --> 00:46:30,474
How long have you been
standing there?

685
00:46:30,476 --> 00:46:31,478
An hour.

686
00:46:32,112 --> 00:46:33,313
An hour?

687
00:46:33,746 --> 00:46:35,313
Are you serious?

688
00:46:35,315 --> 00:46:37,514
I've mastered the ability

689
00:46:37,516 --> 00:46:40,253
of standing
so incredibly still...

690
00:46:41,420 --> 00:46:44,090
that I become
invisible to the eye.

691
00:46:44,590 --> 00:46:45,592
Watch.

692
00:46:49,528 --> 00:46:51,563
You're eating a zarg-nut.

693
00:46:51,565 --> 00:46:53,097
But my movement...

694
00:46:53,766 --> 00:46:55,469
was so slow...

695
00:46:56,335 --> 00:46:58,335
that it's imperceptible.

696
00:46:58,338 --> 00:46:59,204
Mmm, no.

697
00:46:59,206 --> 00:47:01,806
I'm sure I'm invisible.

698
00:47:01,807 --> 00:47:03,141
Hi, Drax.

699
00:47:05,711 --> 00:47:06,713
Damn it.

700
00:47:26,632 --> 00:47:28,565
This place looks deserted.

701
00:47:28,568 --> 00:47:31,503
I'm reading movement
in the third quadrant.

702
00:47:31,505 --> 00:47:33,438
Yep,
I'm picking that up too.

703
00:47:34,773 --> 00:47:36,342
Let's put down right here.

704
00:47:48,152 --> 00:47:49,588
I don't have it.

705
00:47:51,690 --> 00:47:53,523
Everyone
in the galaxy knows

706
00:47:53,525 --> 00:47:55,192
you'd sell your own brother...

707
00:47:55,193 --> 00:47:56,827
if you thought it would add
even the slightest trinket...

708
00:47:56,829 --> 00:47:58,764
to your pathetic collection.

709
00:48:06,605 --> 00:48:10,106
I know you have
the Reality Stone, Tivan.

710
00:48:10,108 --> 00:48:13,478
Giving it to me will spare you
a great deal of suffering.

711
00:48:16,681 --> 00:48:18,349
I told you.

712
00:48:19,184 --> 00:48:20,184
I sold it.

713
00:48:22,889 --> 00:48:25,222
Why would I lie?

714
00:48:25,224 --> 00:48:27,393
I imagine it's like
breathing for you.

715
00:48:28,260 --> 00:48:30,159
Like suicide.

716
00:48:30,161 --> 00:48:32,528
You do understand.

717
00:48:32,530 --> 00:48:35,666
Not even you would surrender
something so precious.

718
00:48:35,668 --> 00:48:37,467
I didn't know what it was.

719
00:48:37,469 --> 00:48:40,436
Then you're more of a fool
than I took you for.

720
00:48:40,438 --> 00:48:41,572
It's him.

721
00:48:41,574 --> 00:48:43,206
Last chance,
charlatan.

722
00:48:44,577 --> 00:48:46,677
Where's the stone?

723
00:48:46,679 --> 00:48:48,210
Today...

724
00:48:48,213 --> 00:48:49,313
Drax. Drax.

725
00:48:49,315 --> 00:48:51,380
he pays for the deaths
of my wife and daughter.

726
00:48:51,382 --> 00:48:52,418
Drax, wait.

727
00:48:53,818 --> 00:48:55,452
Not yet, not yet, not yet.

728
00:48:55,454 --> 00:48:56,655
Drax.

729
00:49:00,559 --> 00:49:02,893
Drax, Drax, Drax.
Listen to me.

730
00:49:02,894 --> 00:49:05,429
He doesn't have the stone yet.

731
00:49:05,431 --> 00:49:07,797
If we get it,
then we can stop him.

732
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:11,268
We have to get
the stone first. Yeah.

733
00:49:11,269 --> 00:49:12,469
No.

734
00:49:12,471 --> 00:49:15,871
No. For Ovette, for Camaria.

735
00:49:15,873 --> 00:49:17,309
Sleep.

736
00:49:29,253 --> 00:49:30,385
Okay.

737
00:49:30,387 --> 00:49:34,460
Gamora, Mantis, you go right.

738
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:37,161
The other right.

739
00:50:01,418 --> 00:50:03,186
Why?

740
00:50:12,998 --> 00:50:17,235
Why you, daughter?

741
00:50:35,753 --> 00:50:36,753
That was quick.

742
00:50:42,592 --> 00:50:47,498
Magnificent! Magnificent!
Magnificent!

743
00:50:49,766 --> 00:50:52,536
Is that sadness
I sense in you, daughter?

744
00:50:55,639 --> 00:50:58,242
In my heart,
I knew you still cared.

745
00:51:05,550 --> 00:51:08,753
But one never knows for sure.

746
00:51:17,929 --> 00:51:20,797
Reality is often
disappointing.

747
00:51:23,934 --> 00:51:26,336
That is, it was.

748
00:51:28,371 --> 00:51:29,673
Now...

749
00:51:31,675 --> 00:51:34,512
reality can be
whatever I want.

750
00:51:35,947 --> 00:51:37,646
You knew I'd come.

751
00:51:37,648 --> 00:51:39,981
I counted on it.

752
00:51:39,983 --> 00:51:42,920
There's something we need
to discuss, little one.

753
00:51:47,625 --> 00:51:49,391
Thanos!

754
00:51:56,867 --> 00:51:57,902
No!

755
00:52:02,405 --> 00:52:04,438
Let her go, Grimace.

756
00:52:04,440 --> 00:52:05,442
Peter.

757
00:52:06,811 --> 00:52:08,012
I told you to go right.

758
00:52:08,679 --> 00:52:10,112
Now? Really?

759
00:52:10,114 --> 00:52:11,981
You let her go!

760
00:52:11,983 --> 00:52:13,882
Ah, the boyfriend.

761
00:52:13,885 --> 00:52:15,018
No.

762
00:52:15,019 --> 00:52:16,416
Like to think of myself

763
00:52:16,418 --> 00:52:18,920
more as a Titan-killing,
long-term booty call.

764
00:52:18,922 --> 00:52:21,090
- Let her go.
- Peter.

765
00:52:21,092 --> 00:52:25,862
I'm gonna blow that nutsack
of a chin right off your face.

766
00:52:26,530 --> 00:52:27,931
Not him.

767
00:52:38,507 --> 00:52:42,079
You promised. You promised.

768
00:52:46,416 --> 00:52:47,949
Oh, daughter.

769
00:52:47,951 --> 00:52:50,554
You expect too much from him.

770
00:52:54,025 --> 00:52:55,692
She's asked, hasn't she?

771
00:52:59,663 --> 00:53:00,664
Do it.

772
00:53:04,534 --> 00:53:05,735
Mmm.

773
00:53:06,969 --> 00:53:08,471
Do it!

774
00:53:15,077 --> 00:53:16,612
I told you to go right.

775
00:53:18,581 --> 00:53:21,550
I love you more than anything.

776
00:53:24,653 --> 00:53:26,056
I love you too.

777
00:53:40,503 --> 00:53:41,538
I like him.

778
00:54:12,036 --> 00:54:14,168
Still no word from Vision?

779
00:54:14,170 --> 00:54:17,570
Satellites lost him
somewhere over Edinburgh.

780
00:54:17,572 --> 00:54:18,806
On a stolen Quinjet

781
00:54:18,807 --> 00:54:20,875
with four of the world's
most wanted criminals.

782
00:54:20,876 --> 00:54:22,608
You know they're
only criminals because

783
00:54:22,610 --> 00:54:24,144
you've chosen to
call them that, right, sir?

784
00:54:24,146 --> 00:54:25,280
My God, Rhodes.

785
00:54:25,282 --> 00:54:28,882
Your talent for horseshit
rivals my own.

786
00:54:28,885 --> 00:54:30,050
If it weren't
for those Accords,

787
00:54:30,052 --> 00:54:32,152
Vision would've been
right here.

788
00:54:32,155 --> 00:54:35,523
I remember your signature
on those papers, Colonel.

789
00:54:35,925 --> 00:54:36,925
That's right.

790
00:54:38,929 --> 00:54:40,929
And I'm pretty sure
I paid for that.

791
00:54:40,931 --> 00:54:42,230
You have second thoughts?

792
00:54:42,231 --> 00:54:44,001
Not anymore.

793
00:54:49,871 --> 00:54:51,539
Mr. Secretary.

794
00:54:55,978 --> 00:54:57,713
You got some nerve.

795
00:54:58,248 --> 00:55:00,081
I'll give you that.

796
00:55:00,083 --> 00:55:01,884
You could use
some of that right now.

797
00:55:02,751 --> 00:55:05,786
The world's on fire.

798
00:55:05,788 --> 00:55:09,523
And you think all is forgiven?

799
00:55:09,525 --> 00:55:11,291
I'm not looking
for forgiveness.

800
00:55:11,293 --> 00:55:13,594
And I'm way past
asking permission.

801
00:55:15,563 --> 00:55:17,998
Earth just lost
her best defender.

802
00:55:18,001 --> 00:55:19,168
So we're here to fight.

803
00:55:20,835 --> 00:55:22,771
And if you wanna
stand in our way...

804
00:55:23,771 --> 00:55:25,708
we'll fight you too.

805
00:55:28,911 --> 00:55:29,911
Arrest them.

806
00:55:31,014 --> 00:55:32,681
All over it.

807
00:55:37,753 --> 00:55:39,054
That's a court-martial.

808
00:55:41,623 --> 00:55:42,702
It's great to see you, Cap.

809
00:55:43,726 --> 00:55:45,592
You too, Rhodey.

810
00:55:45,594 --> 00:55:46,594
Hey.

811
00:55:47,862 --> 00:55:50,099
Wow. You guys...

812
00:55:50,965 --> 00:55:53,099
really look like crap.

813
00:55:53,101 --> 00:55:54,900
Must've been
a rough couple years.

814
00:55:54,902 --> 00:55:58,005
Yeah, well, the hotels
weren't exactly five star.

815
00:55:58,007 --> 00:56:00,141
Uh, I think
you look great.

816
00:56:03,612 --> 00:56:04,679
Uh...

817
00:56:07,215 --> 00:56:09,251
Yeah, I'm back.

818
00:56:10,985 --> 00:56:11,987
Hi, Bruce.

819
00:56:17,625 --> 00:56:18,626
Nat.

820
00:56:21,963 --> 00:56:23,597
This is awkward.

821
00:56:26,001 --> 00:56:27,768
So we gotta assume
they're coming back, right?

822
00:56:27,769 --> 00:56:29,036
And they can clearly find us.

823
00:56:29,039 --> 00:56:31,637
We need all hands on deck.
Where's Clint?

824
00:56:31,639 --> 00:56:33,106
After the whole
Accords situation,

825
00:56:33,108 --> 00:56:34,840
he and Scott took a deal.
It was too tough

826
00:56:34,842 --> 00:56:36,376
on their families.
They're on house arrest.

827
00:56:36,378 --> 00:56:37,943
- Who's Scott?
- Ant-Man.

828
00:56:37,945 --> 00:56:39,347
There's an Ant-Man
and a Spider-Man?

829
00:56:40,248 --> 00:56:41,280
Okay, look.

830
00:56:41,282 --> 00:56:44,351
Thanos has the biggest army
in the universe...

831
00:56:44,353 --> 00:56:47,889
and he is not gonna stop
until he gets...

832
00:56:49,757 --> 00:56:50,923
Vision's stone.

833
00:56:50,925 --> 00:56:52,259
Then we have to protect it.

834
00:56:52,260 --> 00:56:53,961
No, we have to destroy it.

835
00:56:56,097 --> 00:56:57,396
I've been giving
a good deal of thought

836
00:56:57,398 --> 00:56:58,731
to this entity in my head.

837
00:56:58,733 --> 00:57:00,766
About its nature.

838
00:57:00,768 --> 00:57:03,036
But also its composition.

839
00:57:03,039 --> 00:57:05,105
I think if it were exposed

840
00:57:05,106 --> 00:57:07,106
to a sufficiently powerful
energy source...

841
00:57:07,108 --> 00:57:10,978
something very similar to
its own signature, perhaps...

842
00:57:12,646 --> 00:57:15,215
its molecular integrity
could fail.

843
00:57:15,217 --> 00:57:17,983
Yeah, and you with it.

844
00:57:17,985 --> 00:57:19,684
We're not having
this conversation.

845
00:57:19,686 --> 00:57:21,753
Eliminating the stone
is the only way

846
00:57:21,755 --> 00:57:24,190
to be certain that
Thanos can't get it.

847
00:57:24,193 --> 00:57:26,360
That's too high a price.

848
00:57:30,965 --> 00:57:33,268
Only you have
the power to pay it.

849
00:57:37,672 --> 00:57:39,838
Thanos threatens
half the universe.

850
00:57:39,840 --> 00:57:42,409
One life cannot stand
in the way of defeating him.

851
00:57:42,411 --> 00:57:43,945
But it should.

852
00:57:46,347 --> 00:57:47,980
We don't trade lives, Vision.

853
00:57:47,981 --> 00:57:50,081
Captain, 70 years ago,
you laid down your life...

854
00:57:50,083 --> 00:57:52,050
to save how many
millions of people?

855
00:57:52,052 --> 00:57:54,219
Tell me,
why is this any different?

856
00:57:54,222 --> 00:57:56,657
Because you might
have a choice.

857
00:57:57,891 --> 00:57:59,224
Your mind is made up

858
00:57:59,226 --> 00:58:01,860
of a complex construct
of overlays.

859
00:58:01,862 --> 00:58:05,463
Jarvis, Ultron,
Tony, me, the stone.

860
00:58:05,465 --> 00:58:07,333
All of them mixed together,

861
00:58:07,335 --> 00:58:09,235
all of them
learning from one another.

862
00:58:09,237 --> 00:58:11,170
You're saying Vision isn't
just the stone?

863
00:58:11,172 --> 00:58:14,373
I'm saying that
if we take out the stone...

864
00:58:14,375 --> 00:58:15,974
there's still a whole lot
of Vision left.

865
00:58:15,976 --> 00:58:17,809
Perhaps the best parts.

866
00:58:17,811 --> 00:58:19,079
Can we do that?

867
00:58:19,847 --> 00:58:21,880
Not me, not here.

868
00:58:21,882 --> 00:58:23,382
Well,
you better find someone

869
00:58:23,384 --> 00:58:24,849
and somewhere fast.

870
00:58:24,851 --> 00:58:26,217
Ross isn't just gonna
let you guys

871
00:58:26,219 --> 00:58:27,387
have your old rooms back.

872
00:58:30,423 --> 00:58:32,092
I know somewhere.

873
00:58:46,806 --> 00:58:48,072
The Kingsguard

874
00:58:48,074 --> 00:58:49,440
and the Dora Milaje
have been alerted.

875
00:58:49,443 --> 00:58:51,443
And the Border Tribe?

876
00:58:51,445 --> 00:58:53,344
Those that are left.

877
00:58:53,347 --> 00:58:55,780
Send word
to the Jabari as well.

878
00:58:55,782 --> 00:58:57,916
M'Baku likes a good fight.

879
00:59:00,086 --> 00:59:02,353
And what of this one?

880
00:59:02,356 --> 00:59:04,922
This one may be tired of war.

881
00:59:04,925 --> 00:59:07,960
But the White Wolf
has rested long enough.

882
00:59:30,483 --> 00:59:32,152
Where's the fight?

883
00:59:33,085 --> 00:59:34,422
On its way.

884
00:59:52,938 --> 00:59:55,409
In all the time
I've served Thanos...

885
00:59:57,309 --> 00:59:59,311
I have never failed him.

886
01:00:04,384 --> 01:00:07,585
If I were to reach
our rendezvous on Titan...

887
01:00:07,588 --> 01:00:09,320
with the Time Stone
still attached

888
01:00:09,322 --> 01:00:11,590
to your vaguely
irritating person...

889
01:00:11,592 --> 01:00:14,260
there would be judgment.

890
01:00:22,936 --> 01:00:24,371
Give me...

891
01:00:28,240 --> 01:00:29,242
the stone.

892
01:00:41,920 --> 01:00:43,186
Wow, you're a seriously

893
01:00:43,188 --> 01:00:44,389
loyal piece of outerwear,
aren't you?

894
01:00:44,391 --> 01:00:47,057
Yeah, uh,
speaking of loyalty...

895
01:00:47,059 --> 01:00:48,425
What the...

896
01:00:48,427 --> 01:00:50,128
- I know what you're gonna say.
- You should not be here.

897
01:00:50,130 --> 01:00:51,161
- I was gonna go home.
- I don't wanna hear it.

898
01:00:51,164 --> 01:00:52,597
But it was such a long way
down and I just thought

899
01:00:52,599 --> 01:00:53,498
- about you on the way...
- And now I gotta hear it.

900
01:00:53,500 --> 01:00:54,565
and kinda stuck to the side
of the ship.

901
01:00:54,567 --> 01:00:57,135
And this suit is ridiculously
intuitive, by the way.

902
01:00:57,137 --> 01:00:58,268
God damn it.

903
01:00:58,271 --> 01:01:01,239
So, if anything, it's kinda
your fault that I'm here.

904
01:01:01,240 --> 01:01:02,639
- What did you just say?
- I take that back.

905
01:01:02,641 --> 01:01:04,208
And now, I'm here in space.

906
01:01:04,210 --> 01:01:06,876
Yeah, right where
I didn't want you to be.

907
01:01:06,878 --> 01:01:09,079
This isn't Coney Island.
This isn't a field trip.

908
01:01:09,081 --> 01:01:10,213
This is a one-way ticket.

909
01:01:10,215 --> 01:01:12,050
You hear me? Don't pretend
you thought this through.

910
01:01:12,052 --> 01:01:13,150
No, I did think this through.

911
01:01:13,152 --> 01:01:14,951
You could not have possibly
thought this through.

912
01:01:14,952 --> 01:01:16,487
You can't be a friendly
neighborhood Spider-Man...

913
01:01:16,489 --> 01:01:18,157
if there's no neighborhood.

914
01:01:20,293 --> 01:01:21,458
Okay, that didn't
really make sense,

915
01:01:21,460 --> 01:01:22,927
but you know
what I'm trying to say.

916
01:01:25,030 --> 01:01:28,931
Come on. We got a situation.

917
01:01:28,934 --> 01:01:30,001
See him down there?
He's in trouble.

918
01:01:30,003 --> 01:01:31,068
What's your plan?

919
01:01:31,070 --> 01:01:32,204
- Go.
- Um...

920
01:01:32,938 --> 01:01:34,505
Okay, okay... Uh...

921
01:01:34,507 --> 01:01:37,940
Okay. Did you ever see
this really old movie, Aliens?

922
01:01:41,447 --> 01:01:44,349
Painful, aren't they?

923
01:01:44,351 --> 01:01:48,050
They were originally designed
for microsurgery.

924
01:01:48,052 --> 01:01:50,121
And any one of them...

925
01:01:55,193 --> 01:01:58,028
could end your friend's life
in an instant.

926
01:01:58,030 --> 01:01:59,664
I gotta tell you,
he's not really my friend.

927
01:01:59,666 --> 01:02:02,402
Saving his life is more
of a professional courtesy.

928
01:02:04,235 --> 01:02:06,936
You've saved nothing.

929
01:02:06,938 --> 01:02:09,005
Your powers
are inconsequential

930
01:02:09,007 --> 01:02:10,507
compared to mine.

931
01:02:10,510 --> 01:02:12,210
Yeah, but the kid's
seen more movies.

932
01:02:26,358 --> 01:02:28,494
Yes! Wait.
What are those?

933
01:02:44,208 --> 01:02:45,978
Hey,
we haven't officially met.

934
01:02:47,211 --> 01:02:48,280
Cool.

935
01:02:50,282 --> 01:02:51,748
We gotta turn
this ship around.

936
01:02:51,750 --> 01:02:54,117
Yeah, now he wants
to run. Great plan.

937
01:02:54,119 --> 01:02:55,552
No, I want to protect
the stone.

938
01:02:55,554 --> 01:02:56,987
And I want you
to thank me.

939
01:02:56,989 --> 01:02:58,521
Now, go ahead. I'm listening.

940
01:02:58,523 --> 01:03:01,425
For what?
Nearly blasting me into space?

941
01:03:01,427 --> 01:03:03,760
Who just saved
your magical ass? Me.

942
01:03:03,762 --> 01:03:04,628
I seriously don't know

943
01:03:04,630 --> 01:03:05,795
how you fit your head
into that helmet.

944
01:03:05,797 --> 01:03:08,632
Admit it, you should've
ducked out when I told you to.

945
01:03:08,634 --> 01:03:10,367
I tried to bench you.
You refused.

946
01:03:10,369 --> 01:03:12,436
Unlike everyone else in your
life, I don't work for you.

947
01:03:12,438 --> 01:03:14,170
And due to that fact,

948
01:03:14,172 --> 01:03:15,572
we're now
in a flying doughnut...

949
01:03:15,574 --> 01:03:17,440
billions of miles from Earth
with no backup.

950
01:03:17,443 --> 01:03:19,509
- I'm backup.
- No, you're a stowaway.

951
01:03:19,510 --> 01:03:20,577
The adults are talking.

952
01:03:20,579 --> 01:03:23,447
I'm sorry, I'm confused
as to the relationship here.

953
01:03:23,449 --> 01:03:25,282
What is he, your ward?

954
01:03:25,284 --> 01:03:26,682
No.

955
01:03:26,684 --> 01:03:28,717
- I'm Peter, by the way.
- Doctor Strange.

956
01:03:28,719 --> 01:03:30,489
Oh, you're using
our made-up names. Um...

957
01:03:31,456 --> 01:03:33,590
I'm Spider-Man, then.

958
01:03:33,592 --> 01:03:35,257
This ship is
self-correcting its course.

959
01:03:35,260 --> 01:03:36,393
Thing's on autopilot.

960
01:03:36,394 --> 01:03:38,295
Can we control it?

961
01:03:38,297 --> 01:03:40,231
Fly us home?

962
01:03:43,235 --> 01:03:44,367
- Stark?
- Yeah.

963
01:03:44,369 --> 01:03:45,702
Can you get us home?

964
01:03:45,704 --> 01:03:47,103
Yeah, I heard you.

965
01:03:48,340 --> 01:03:50,708
I'm thinking I'm not
so sure we should.

966
01:03:51,443 --> 01:03:53,108
Under no circumstances

967
01:03:53,110 --> 01:03:55,679
can we bring
the Time Stone to Thanos.

968
01:03:55,681 --> 01:03:57,079
I don't think
you quite understand

969
01:03:57,081 --> 01:03:58,014
what's at stake here.

970
01:03:58,016 --> 01:04:00,617
What? No. It's you
who doesn't understand...

971
01:04:00,619 --> 01:04:03,552
that Thanos has been
inside my head for six years.

972
01:04:03,554 --> 01:04:05,286
Since he sent an army
to New York

973
01:04:05,289 --> 01:04:07,056
and now he's back.

974
01:04:07,057 --> 01:04:09,123
And I don't know what to do.

975
01:04:09,126 --> 01:04:10,259
So I'm not so sure

976
01:04:10,260 --> 01:04:12,293
if it's a better plan to fight
him on our turf or his...

977
01:04:12,295 --> 01:04:16,130
but you saw what they did,
what they can do.

978
01:04:16,132 --> 01:04:18,434
At least on his turf,
he's not expecting it.

979
01:04:18,436 --> 01:04:21,369
So I say we take
the fight to him.

980
01:04:21,371 --> 01:04:22,373
Doctor.

981
01:04:24,141 --> 01:04:25,677
Do you concur?

982
01:04:28,246 --> 01:04:30,715
All right, Stark.
We go to him.

983
01:04:31,782 --> 01:04:34,148
But you have to understand...

984
01:04:34,150 --> 01:04:35,751
if it comes to saving you

985
01:04:35,753 --> 01:04:38,454
or the kid
or the Time Stone...

986
01:04:38,456 --> 01:04:42,190
I will not hesitate
to let either of you die.

987
01:04:42,193 --> 01:04:46,394
I can't, because the universe
depends on it.

988
01:04:46,396 --> 01:04:49,300
Nice. Good, moral compass.

989
01:04:50,534 --> 01:04:52,135
We're straight.

990
01:04:53,237 --> 01:04:54,639
All right, kid.

991
01:04:55,873 --> 01:04:57,108
You're an Avenger now.

992
01:05:33,577 --> 01:05:35,813
I thought
you might be hungry.

993
01:05:47,925 --> 01:05:49,724
I always hated that chair.

994
01:05:49,726 --> 01:05:52,494
So I've been told.

995
01:05:52,496 --> 01:05:56,434
Even so, I'd hoped you'd
sit in it one day.

996
01:05:57,233 --> 01:05:58,668
I hated this room.

997
01:05:59,570 --> 01:06:00,936
This ship.

998
01:06:00,938 --> 01:06:02,773
I hated my life.

999
01:06:07,309 --> 01:06:09,512
You told me that too.

1000
01:06:12,650 --> 01:06:14,150
Every day.

1001
01:06:16,786 --> 01:06:18,755
For almost 20 years.

1002
01:06:21,391 --> 01:06:23,728
I was a child
when you took me.

1003
01:06:24,628 --> 01:06:25,896
I saved you.

1004
01:06:29,498 --> 01:06:30,498
No.

1005
01:06:31,902 --> 01:06:35,670
No. We were happy
on my home planet.

1006
01:06:35,672 --> 01:06:37,405
Going to bed hungry...

1007
01:06:37,407 --> 01:06:39,306
scrounging for scraps.

1008
01:06:39,309 --> 01:06:42,275
Your planet was
on the brink of collapse.

1009
01:06:42,277 --> 01:06:44,713
I'm the one who stopped that.

1010
01:06:44,715 --> 01:06:46,715
Do you know
what's happened since then?

1011
01:06:46,717 --> 01:06:48,916
The children born...

1012
01:06:48,918 --> 01:06:52,552
have known nothing but
full bellies and clear skies.

1013
01:06:52,554 --> 01:06:53,757
It's a paradise.

1014
01:06:56,492 --> 01:06:58,525
Because you murdered
half the planet.

1015
01:06:58,527 --> 01:07:01,561
A small price to pay
for salvation.

1016
01:07:01,563 --> 01:07:02,697
You're insane.

1017
01:07:02,699 --> 01:07:04,798
Little one,
it's a simple calculus.

1018
01:07:04,800 --> 01:07:08,268
This universe is finite,
its resources finite.

1019
01:07:08,271 --> 01:07:12,606
If life is left unchecked,
life will cease to exist.

1020
01:07:12,608 --> 01:07:13,807
It needs correction.

1021
01:07:13,809 --> 01:07:15,311
You don't know that!

1022
01:07:16,746 --> 01:07:19,614
I'm the only one
who knows that.

1023
01:07:19,615 --> 01:07:23,786
At least, I'm the only one
with the will to act on it.

1024
01:07:25,454 --> 01:07:26,456
For a time...

1025
01:07:28,925 --> 01:07:33,329
you had that same will...

1026
01:07:34,797 --> 01:07:37,333
as you fought by my side.

1027
01:07:38,034 --> 01:07:39,268
Daughter.

1028
01:07:39,902 --> 01:07:41,737
I'm not your daughter.

1029
01:07:44,273 --> 01:07:46,876
Everything I hate about myself
you taught me.

1030
01:07:47,710 --> 01:07:49,309
And, in doing so,

1031
01:07:49,311 --> 01:07:51,514
made you the fiercest woman
in the galaxy.

1032
01:07:54,451 --> 01:07:57,320
That's why I trusted you
to find the Soul Stone.

1033
01:08:00,623 --> 01:08:03,490
I'm sorry I disappointed you.

1034
01:08:04,626 --> 01:08:07,293
I am disappointed.

1035
01:08:07,295 --> 01:08:09,666
But not because
you didn't find it.

1036
01:08:13,436 --> 01:08:14,938
But because you did.

1037
01:08:16,506 --> 01:08:18,306
And you lied.

1038
01:08:35,390 --> 01:08:36,492
Nebula.

1039
01:08:43,699 --> 01:08:45,099
Don't do this.

1040
01:08:45,100 --> 01:08:46,533
Some time ago,

1041
01:08:46,534 --> 01:08:49,435
your sister snuck aboard
this ship to kill me.

1042
01:08:49,438 --> 01:08:50,503
Please don't do this.

1043
01:08:50,506 --> 01:08:52,742
And very nearly succeeded.

1044
01:08:53,475 --> 01:08:54,844
So I brought her here.

1045
01:08:56,478 --> 01:08:57,679
To talk.

1046
01:09:05,386 --> 01:09:07,722
Stop. Stop it.

1047
01:09:13,628 --> 01:09:16,496
I swear to you on my life.

1048
01:09:16,497 --> 01:09:18,734
I never found the Soul Stone.

1049
01:09:22,837 --> 01:09:24,637
Accessing memory files.

1050
01:09:24,640 --> 01:09:26,041
You know
what he's about to do.

1051
01:09:26,042 --> 01:09:28,841
He's finally ready,
and he's going for the stones.

1052
01:09:28,844 --> 01:09:30,045
- All of them.
- He can never get them all.

1053
01:09:30,046 --> 01:09:31,112
He will!

1054
01:09:31,113 --> 01:09:33,412
He can't, Nebula.

1055
01:09:33,414 --> 01:09:35,815
Because I found the map
to the Soul Stone...

1056
01:09:35,818 --> 01:09:38,654
and I burned it to ash.
I burned it.

1057
01:09:43,692 --> 01:09:45,527
You're strong.

1058
01:09:47,563 --> 01:09:48,564
Me.

1059
01:09:51,033 --> 01:09:52,701
You're generous.

1060
01:09:53,969 --> 01:09:54,970
Me.

1061
01:09:56,971 --> 01:09:59,639
But I never taught you to lie.

1062
01:09:59,640 --> 01:10:02,344
That's why
you're so bad at it.

1063
01:10:04,512 --> 01:10:08,951
Where is the Soul Stone?

1064
01:10:26,467 --> 01:10:27,469
Vormir!

1065
01:10:45,587 --> 01:10:47,055
The stone is on Vormir.

1066
01:10:50,490 --> 01:10:52,860
Show me.

1067
01:10:54,729 --> 01:10:56,128
I am Groot.

1068
01:10:56,131 --> 01:10:57,496
Tinkle in the cup.

1069
01:10:57,497 --> 01:10:58,899
We're not looking.
What's there to see?

1070
01:10:58,900 --> 01:11:01,167
What's a twig? Everybody's
seen a twig before.

1071
01:11:01,168 --> 01:11:02,568
I am Groot.

1072
01:11:02,569 --> 01:11:03,668
Tree, pour what's in the cup

1073
01:11:03,671 --> 01:11:05,503
out into space
and go in the cup again.

1074
01:11:05,506 --> 01:11:06,604
You speak Groot?

1075
01:11:06,606 --> 01:11:08,774
Yes, they taught it on Asgard.
It was an elective.

1076
01:11:08,777 --> 01:11:09,943
I am Groot.

1077
01:11:09,944 --> 01:11:12,078
You'll know when we're close.

1078
01:11:12,079 --> 01:11:13,813
Nidavellir's forge harnesses

1079
01:11:13,814 --> 01:11:15,984
the blazing power
of a neutron star.

1080
01:11:18,854 --> 01:11:20,854
It's the birthplace
of my hammer.

1081
01:11:21,622 --> 01:11:23,423
It's truly awesome.

1082
01:11:29,264 --> 01:11:32,565
Okay, time to be the captain.

1083
01:11:37,570 --> 01:11:39,738
So, dead brother, huh?

1084
01:11:39,739 --> 01:11:42,007
Yeah, that could be annoying.

1085
01:11:42,010 --> 01:11:43,911
Well, he's been dead before.

1086
01:11:45,279 --> 01:11:48,280
But, no, this time I think
it really might be true.

1087
01:11:48,283 --> 01:11:50,882
And you said
your sister and your dad?

1088
01:11:50,885 --> 01:11:52,818
Both dead.

1089
01:11:52,819 --> 01:11:54,953
But still got a mom, though?

1090
01:11:54,956 --> 01:11:56,288
Killed by a dark elf.

1091
01:11:56,291 --> 01:11:57,588
A best friend?

1092
01:11:57,591 --> 01:11:58,859
Stabbed through the heart.

1093
01:12:02,162 --> 01:12:05,498
You sure you're up to this
particular murder mission?

1094
01:12:07,702 --> 01:12:09,201
Absolutely.

1095
01:12:09,203 --> 01:12:12,938
Rage and vengeance,
anger, loss, regret...

1096
01:12:12,939 --> 01:12:14,672
they're all
tremendous motivators.

1097
01:12:14,675 --> 01:12:15,807
They really clear the mind.

1098
01:12:15,810 --> 01:12:18,043
So I'm good to go.

1099
01:12:18,046 --> 01:12:20,746
Yeah, but this Thanos
we're talkin' about...

1100
01:12:20,747 --> 01:12:23,114
he's the toughest there is.

1101
01:12:23,117 --> 01:12:25,283
- Well, he's never fought me.
- Yeah, he has.

1102
01:12:25,286 --> 01:12:27,618
He's never fought me twice.

1103
01:12:27,621 --> 01:12:29,555
And I'm getting a new hammer,
don't forget.

1104
01:12:29,556 --> 01:12:31,759
It better be some hammer.

1105
01:12:35,863 --> 01:12:38,896
You know, I'm 1,500 years old.

1106
01:12:38,899 --> 01:12:41,065
I've killed twice
as many enemies as that.

1107
01:12:41,068 --> 01:12:43,101
And every one of them
would've rather killed me,

1108
01:12:43,104 --> 01:12:44,837
but none succeeded.

1109
01:12:44,838 --> 01:12:47,905
I'm only alive
because fate wants me alive.

1110
01:12:47,908 --> 01:12:50,876
Thanos is just the latest
in a long line of bastards...

1111
01:12:50,877 --> 01:12:52,911
and he'll be the latest
to feel my vengeance.

1112
01:12:52,912 --> 01:12:54,813
Fate wills it so.

1113
01:12:54,814 --> 01:12:56,148
Mmm-hmm.

1114
01:12:56,149 --> 01:12:58,020
And what if you're wrong?

1115
01:13:01,255 --> 01:13:03,090
If I'm wrong, then...

1116
01:13:04,324 --> 01:13:05,960
what more could I lose?

1117
01:13:19,806 --> 01:13:21,172
I could lose a lot.

1118
01:13:21,175 --> 01:13:23,277
Me, personally,
I could lose a lot.

1119
01:13:27,113 --> 01:13:28,114
Okay.

1120
01:13:31,185 --> 01:13:33,385
If fate does want you
to kill that crapsack...

1121
01:13:33,386 --> 01:13:35,287
you're gonna need more
than one stupid eyeball.

1122
01:13:35,288 --> 01:13:37,755
- What's this?
- What's it look like?

1123
01:13:37,756 --> 01:13:40,359
Some jerk lost a bet with me
on Contraxia.

1124
01:13:40,360 --> 01:13:41,759
He gave you his eye?

1125
01:13:41,761 --> 01:13:42,994
No, he gave me 100 credits.

1126
01:13:42,997 --> 01:13:45,965
I snuck into his room later
that night and stole his eye.

1127
01:13:47,900 --> 01:13:49,167
Thank you, sweet rabbit.

1128
01:13:49,170 --> 01:13:50,171
Hmm.

1129
01:13:52,805 --> 01:13:54,207
Huh?

1130
01:13:56,042 --> 01:13:57,341
Oh.

1131
01:13:57,344 --> 01:14:00,145
I would've washed that.

1132
01:14:00,146 --> 01:14:02,814
The only way I could sneak it
off Contraxia was up my...

1133
01:14:04,018 --> 01:14:05,085
Hey, we're here!

1134
01:14:09,088 --> 01:14:10,322
I don't think
this thing works.

1135
01:14:10,323 --> 01:14:11,658
Everything seems dark.

1136
01:14:14,028 --> 01:14:15,795
It ain't the eye.

1137
01:14:29,074 --> 01:14:30,377
Something's wrong.

1138
01:14:31,211 --> 01:14:32,845
The star's gone out.

1139
01:14:33,947 --> 01:14:35,180
And the rings are frozen.

1140
01:14:56,301 --> 01:14:57,935
I hope
these dwarves are better

1141
01:14:57,936 --> 01:14:59,804
at forging
than they are cleaning.

1142
01:15:04,944 --> 01:15:06,476
Maybe they realized
that they live

1143
01:15:06,479 --> 01:15:08,145
in a junk pile
in the middle of space.

1144
01:15:08,148 --> 01:15:11,117
This forge hasn't gone dark
in centuries.

1145
01:15:13,353 --> 01:15:16,186
You said Thanos
had a gauntlet, right?

1146
01:15:16,189 --> 01:15:17,454
Yes, why?

1147
01:15:17,457 --> 01:15:19,690
It look
anything like that?

1148
01:15:23,029 --> 01:15:24,962
I am Groot.

1149
01:15:24,963 --> 01:15:26,365
Go back to the pod.

1150
01:15:30,369 --> 01:15:31,404
Eitri, wait!

1151
01:15:32,404 --> 01:15:33,405
Stop!

1152
01:15:34,340 --> 01:15:35,341
Stop.

1153
01:15:36,109 --> 01:15:37,109
Thor?

1154
01:15:40,380 --> 01:15:42,212
What happened here?

1155
01:15:42,215 --> 01:15:45,382
You were supposed
to protect us.

1156
01:15:45,385 --> 01:15:48,219
Asgard was supposed
to protect us.

1157
01:15:48,220 --> 01:15:50,390
Asgard is destroyed.

1158
01:15:52,791 --> 01:15:56,462
Eitri, the glove.
What did you do?

1159
01:16:09,274 --> 01:16:12,278
300 dwarves
lived on this ring.

1160
01:16:13,779 --> 01:16:16,715
I thought if I did what
he asked, they'd be safe.

1161
01:16:19,117 --> 01:16:20,485
I made what he wanted.

1162
01:16:22,253 --> 01:16:26,725
A device capable of harnessing
the power of the stones.

1163
01:16:31,162 --> 01:16:33,832
Then he killed
everyone anyway.

1164
01:16:35,900 --> 01:16:37,735
All except me.

1165
01:16:38,804 --> 01:16:40,506
"Your life is yours," he said.

1166
01:16:41,939 --> 01:16:46,876
"But your hands
are mine alone."

1167
01:16:46,877 --> 01:16:48,880
Eitri, this isn't about
your hands.

1168
01:16:49,981 --> 01:16:51,515
Every weapon
you've ever designed,

1169
01:16:51,516 --> 01:16:53,182
every axe, hammer, sword...

1170
01:16:53,185 --> 01:16:56,252
it's all inside your head.

1171
01:16:56,255 --> 01:16:58,320
Now, I know it feels
like all hope is lost.

1172
01:16:58,323 --> 01:17:00,323
Trust me, I know.

1173
01:17:00,324 --> 01:17:05,096
But together, you and I,
we can kill Thanos.

1174
01:17:45,503 --> 01:17:48,070
Mantis, listen very carefully.

1175
01:17:48,073 --> 01:17:50,242
I need you
to meet me on Titan.

1176
01:17:56,881 --> 01:17:58,113
Hey, what's going on?

1177
01:17:58,115 --> 01:17:59,416
I think we're here.

1178
01:17:59,417 --> 01:18:01,985
I don't think this rig has
a self-park function.

1179
01:18:03,587 --> 01:18:05,287
Get your hand
inside the steering gimbal.

1180
01:18:05,289 --> 01:18:06,324
Close those around it.

1181
01:18:08,059 --> 01:18:09,225
- You understand?
- Yep, got it.

1182
01:18:09,226 --> 01:18:10,527
This was meant for
one big guy, so we gotta

1183
01:18:10,529 --> 01:18:12,289
- move at the same time.
- Okay, okay. Ready.

1184
01:18:16,600 --> 01:18:18,100
We might wanna turn.

1185
01:18:18,101 --> 01:18:19,304
Turn! Turn! Turn!

1186
01:18:49,265 --> 01:18:50,868
You all right?

1187
01:18:51,703 --> 01:18:53,471
That was close.

1188
01:18:54,971 --> 01:18:56,573
I owe you one.

1189
01:18:56,574 --> 01:18:58,707
Let me just say, if aliens

1190
01:18:58,710 --> 01:19:00,643
wind up implanting eggs
in my chest or something...

1191
01:19:00,645 --> 01:19:01,677
and I eat one of you,
I'm sorry.

1192
01:19:01,680 --> 01:19:04,412
I do not want another
single pop culture reference

1193
01:19:04,414 --> 01:19:06,148
out of you for the rest
of the trip. You understand?

1194
01:19:06,149 --> 01:19:07,829
I'm trying to say
that something is coming.

1195
01:19:15,059 --> 01:19:16,127
Thanos!

1196
01:19:36,980 --> 01:19:39,047
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Please don't
put your eggs in me!

1197
01:19:40,384 --> 01:19:42,953
Stay down, clown.

1198
01:19:48,125 --> 01:19:50,194
Die, blanket of death!

1199
01:19:56,132 --> 01:19:59,069
Everybody stay where
you are. Chill the eff out.

1200
01:20:00,237 --> 01:20:02,238
I'm gonna ask you
this one time.

1201
01:20:03,041 --> 01:20:04,372
Where is Gamora?

1202
01:20:04,375 --> 01:20:07,208
Yeah. I'll do you one better.
Who's Gamora?

1203
01:20:07,211 --> 01:20:10,179
I'll do you one better.
Why is Gamora?

1204
01:20:10,180 --> 01:20:12,180
Tell me where the girl is
or I swear to you

1205
01:20:12,182 --> 01:20:13,448
I'm gonna French fry
this little freak.

1206
01:20:13,451 --> 01:20:17,051
Let's do it. You shoot my guy
and I'll blast him. Let's go!

1207
01:20:17,052 --> 01:20:19,654
Do it, Quill! I can take it.

1208
01:20:19,657 --> 01:20:21,789
- No, he can't take it!
- She's right. You can't.

1209
01:20:21,792 --> 01:20:24,158
Oh, yeah? You don't wanna tell
me where she is? That's fine.

1210
01:20:24,159 --> 01:20:25,260
I'll kill all three of you

1211
01:20:25,261 --> 01:20:27,261
and I'll beat it
out of Thanos myself.

1212
01:20:27,264 --> 01:20:28,329
Starting with you.

1213
01:20:28,332 --> 01:20:29,264
Wait, what, Thanos?

1214
01:20:29,265 --> 01:20:32,132
All right, let me ask you
this one time.

1215
01:20:32,135 --> 01:20:33,801
What master do you serve?

1216
01:20:33,804 --> 01:20:35,269
What master do I serve?

1217
01:20:35,270 --> 01:20:36,640
What am I supposed to say,
"Jesus"?

1218
01:20:37,608 --> 01:20:38,506
You're from Earth.

1219
01:20:38,509 --> 01:20:39,408
I'm not from Earth,
I'm from Missouri.

1220
01:20:39,409 --> 01:20:41,376
Yeah, that's on Earth,
dipshit.

1221
01:20:41,377 --> 01:20:42,543
What are you hassling us for?

1222
01:20:42,546 --> 01:20:44,346
So you're not
with Thanos?

1223
01:20:44,747 --> 01:20:47,247
With Thanos?

1224
01:20:47,250 --> 01:20:50,051
No, I'm here to kill Thanos.

1225
01:20:50,052 --> 01:20:52,587
He took my girl.
Wait, who are you?

1226
01:20:52,590 --> 01:20:54,421
- We're the Avengers, man.
- Oh.

1227
01:20:54,423 --> 01:20:56,792
You're the ones
Thor told us about.

1228
01:20:56,793 --> 01:20:58,259
You know Thor?

1229
01:20:58,261 --> 01:20:59,226
Yeah.

1230
01:20:59,229 --> 01:21:02,095
Tall guy, not that
good-looking, needed saving.

1231
01:21:02,097 --> 01:21:03,634
Where is he now?

1232
01:21:18,681 --> 01:21:20,716
This is the plan? We're gonna
hit him with a brick?

1233
01:21:20,717 --> 01:21:22,085
It's a mold.

1234
01:21:22,685 --> 01:21:24,652
A king's weapon.

1235
01:21:24,654 --> 01:21:27,622
Meant to be
the greatest in Asgard.

1236
01:21:27,623 --> 01:21:30,658
In theory, it could even
summon the Bifrost.

1237
01:21:30,659 --> 01:21:32,228
Did it have a name?

1238
01:21:33,429 --> 01:21:35,128
Stormbreaker.

1239
01:21:35,131 --> 01:21:36,231
That's a bit much.

1240
01:21:38,268 --> 01:21:39,335
So how do we make it?

1241
01:21:41,203 --> 01:21:43,372
You'll have to restart
the forge.

1242
01:21:44,340 --> 01:21:46,509
Awaken the heart
of a dying star.

1243
01:21:49,212 --> 01:21:51,713
Rabbit, fire up the pod.

1244
01:21:55,451 --> 01:21:57,551
The hell happened
to this planet?

1245
01:21:57,554 --> 01:21:59,453
It's eight degrees
off its axis.

1246
01:21:59,454 --> 01:22:01,623
Gravitational pull
is all over the place.

1247
01:22:02,891 --> 01:22:06,694
Yeah, we got one advantage.
He's coming to us.

1248
01:22:06,695 --> 01:22:09,529
We'll use it.
All right, I have a plan.

1249
01:22:09,532 --> 01:22:10,864
Or at least
the beginnings of one.

1250
01:22:10,867 --> 01:22:12,399
It's pretty simple.
We draw him in,

1251
01:22:12,402 --> 01:22:13,701
pin him down,
get what we need.

1252
01:22:13,703 --> 01:22:15,502
Definitely don't wanna
dance with this guy.

1253
01:22:15,505 --> 01:22:17,203
We just want the gauntlet.

1254
01:22:17,206 --> 01:22:19,573
Are you yawning?

1255
01:22:19,576 --> 01:22:21,841
In the middle of this, while
I'm breaking it down? Huh?

1256
01:22:21,844 --> 01:22:23,677
Did you hear what I said?

1257
01:22:23,680 --> 01:22:26,212
I stopped listening after
you said, "We need a plan."

1258
01:22:26,215 --> 01:22:27,280
Okay, Mr. Clean
is on his own page.

1259
01:22:27,283 --> 01:22:30,417
See, "not winging it"
isn't really what they do.

1260
01:22:30,420 --> 01:22:32,152
Uh, what exactly
is it that they do?

1261
01:22:32,154 --> 01:22:33,753
Kick names, take ass.

1262
01:22:33,756 --> 01:22:35,157
Yeah, that's right.

1263
01:22:41,730 --> 01:22:43,530
All right, just get over here,
please.

1264
01:22:43,533 --> 01:22:45,600
Mr. Lord, can you get
your folks to circle up?

1265
01:22:45,601 --> 01:22:47,737
"Mr. Lord." Star-Lord is fine.

1266
01:22:50,506 --> 01:22:51,872
We gotta coalesce.

1267
01:22:51,873 --> 01:22:53,707
'Cause if all we come at him
with is a plucky attitude...

1268
01:22:53,710 --> 01:22:56,275
Dude, don't call us plucky.

1269
01:22:56,278 --> 01:22:57,744
We don't know what it means.

1270
01:22:57,747 --> 01:23:00,547
All right, we're optimistic,
yes. I like your plan.

1271
01:23:00,550 --> 01:23:03,248
Except it sucks,
so let me do the plan...

1272
01:23:03,251 --> 01:23:05,318
and that way
it might be really good.

1273
01:23:05,319 --> 01:23:07,420
Tell him about the dance-off
to save the universe.

1274
01:23:07,421 --> 01:23:09,657
- What dance-off?
- It's nothing.

1275
01:23:09,658 --> 01:23:10,824
Like in Footloose, the movie?

1276
01:23:10,827 --> 01:23:12,760
Exactly like Footloose.

1277
01:23:12,761 --> 01:23:14,493
Is it still the greatest movie
in history?

1278
01:23:14,496 --> 01:23:15,729
It never was.

1279
01:23:15,731 --> 01:23:16,831
Don't encourage this,
all right?

1280
01:23:16,832 --> 01:23:18,331
- Okay.
- We're getting no help

1281
01:23:18,332 --> 01:23:19,867
- from Flash Gordon here.
- Flash Gordon?

1282
01:23:19,868 --> 01:23:21,636
By the way,
that's a compliment.

1283
01:23:21,637 --> 01:23:23,369
Don't forget, I'm half human.

1284
01:23:23,372 --> 01:23:24,806
So that 50% of me
that's stupid...

1285
01:23:25,975 --> 01:23:27,306
that's 100% you.

1286
01:23:27,309 --> 01:23:28,574
Your math
is blowing my mind.

1287
01:23:28,577 --> 01:23:29,811
Excuse me.

1288
01:23:30,813 --> 01:23:34,349
But does your friend
often do that?

1289
01:23:35,684 --> 01:23:37,920
Strange, we all right?

1290
01:23:48,363 --> 01:23:49,462
You're back. You're all right.

1291
01:23:49,463 --> 01:23:51,698
- Hi.
- Hey, what was that?

1292
01:23:51,699 --> 01:23:56,336
I went forward in time
to view alternate futures.

1293
01:23:56,337 --> 01:23:57,837
To see all
the possible outcomes

1294
01:23:57,838 --> 01:23:59,707
of the coming conflict.

1295
01:24:00,509 --> 01:24:01,908
How many did you see?

1296
01:24:01,909 --> 01:24:04,311
14,000,605.

1297
01:24:05,846 --> 01:24:07,381
How many did we win?

1298
01:24:11,987 --> 01:24:13,320
One.

1299
01:24:35,043 --> 01:24:38,246
The stone
had better be up there.

1300
01:24:39,948 --> 01:24:41,983
For your sister's sake.

1301
01:25:02,904 --> 01:25:07,708
Welcome, Thanos, son of Alars.

1302
01:25:09,778 --> 01:25:13,311
Gamora, daughter of Thanos.

1303
01:25:13,314 --> 01:25:14,581
You know us?

1304
01:25:14,582 --> 01:25:19,618
It is my curse to know all
who journey here.

1305
01:25:19,621 --> 01:25:21,354
Where is the Soul Stone?

1306
01:25:21,922 --> 01:25:24,389
You should know...

1307
01:25:24,390 --> 01:25:27,494
it extracts a terrible price.

1308
01:25:28,764 --> 01:25:30,430
I am prepared.

1309
01:25:32,801 --> 01:25:35,336
We all think that at first.

1310
01:25:39,774 --> 01:25:42,011
We are all wrong.

1311
01:25:53,686 --> 01:25:56,088
How is it you know
this place so well?

1312
01:25:56,091 --> 01:26:00,926
A lifetime ago,
I, too, sought the stones.

1313
01:26:00,929 --> 01:26:03,828
I even held one in my hand.

1314
01:26:03,831 --> 01:26:08,002
But it cast me out,
banished me here.

1315
01:26:08,003 --> 01:26:12,041
Guiding others to a treasure
I cannot possess.

1316
01:26:20,814 --> 01:26:23,751
What you seek
lies in front of you.

1317
01:26:24,717 --> 01:26:26,820
As does what you fear.

1318
01:26:27,621 --> 01:26:29,587
What's this?

1319
01:26:29,590 --> 01:26:31,157
The price.

1320
01:26:31,158 --> 01:26:36,862
Soul holds a special place
among the Infinity Stones.

1321
01:26:36,863 --> 01:26:40,935
You might say it has
a certain wisdom.

1322
01:26:42,435 --> 01:26:44,435
Tell me what it needs.

1323
01:26:44,438 --> 01:26:48,006
To ensure that
whoever possesses it...

1324
01:26:48,009 --> 01:26:50,644
understands its power...

1325
01:26:51,612 --> 01:26:55,546
the stone demands a sacrifice.

1326
01:26:55,548 --> 01:26:57,515
Of what?

1327
01:26:57,518 --> 01:26:59,551
In order to take the stone,

1328
01:26:59,552 --> 01:27:01,889
you must lose
that which you love.

1329
01:27:04,824 --> 01:27:06,060
A soul...

1330
01:27:06,793 --> 01:27:07,994
for a soul.

1331
01:27:23,777 --> 01:27:26,046
All my life,
I dreamed of a day...

1332
01:27:27,015 --> 01:27:28,514
a moment...

1333
01:27:29,783 --> 01:27:31,851
when you got
what you deserved.

1334
01:27:34,021 --> 01:27:36,456
And I was always
so disappointed.

1335
01:27:39,926 --> 01:27:41,493
But now...

1336
01:27:45,465 --> 01:27:48,533
You kill and torture...

1337
01:27:50,502 --> 01:27:52,505
and you call it mercy.

1338
01:27:56,576 --> 01:27:58,645
The universe has judged you.

1339
01:28:00,113 --> 01:28:04,684
You asked it for a prize,
and it told you no.

1340
01:28:06,119 --> 01:28:07,720
You failed.

1341
01:28:09,024 --> 01:28:10,925
And do you wanna know why?

1342
01:28:11,890 --> 01:28:13,760
Because you love nothing.

1343
01:28:14,527 --> 01:28:16,030
No one.

1344
01:28:21,734 --> 01:28:22,868
No.

1345
01:28:27,573 --> 01:28:28,573
Really?

1346
01:28:29,609 --> 01:28:30,676
Tears?

1347
01:28:31,511 --> 01:28:33,479
They're not for him.

1348
01:28:47,694 --> 01:28:48,860
No.

1349
01:28:50,264 --> 01:28:51,797
This isn't love.

1350
01:28:52,698 --> 01:28:55,234
I ignored my destiny once.

1351
01:28:57,804 --> 01:28:59,939
I cannot do that again.

1352
01:29:00,539 --> 01:29:03,842
Even for you.

1353
01:29:28,002 --> 01:29:30,302
I'm sorry, little one.

1354
01:29:34,172 --> 01:29:35,573
No!

1355
01:31:13,070 --> 01:31:16,072
Drop to 2600, heading 0-3-0.

1356
01:31:16,073 --> 01:31:17,407
I hope you're right
about this.

1357
01:31:17,408 --> 01:31:20,311
Or we're gonna land
a lot faster than you want to.

1358
01:31:36,094 --> 01:31:37,460
When you said we were
going to open Wakanda

1359
01:31:37,462 --> 01:31:38,862
to the rest of the world...

1360
01:31:38,863 --> 01:31:41,163
this is not what I imagined.

1361
01:31:41,166 --> 01:31:43,265
And what did you imagine?

1362
01:31:43,268 --> 01:31:44,701
The Olympics.

1363
01:31:44,703 --> 01:31:46,304
Maybe even a Starbucks.

1364
01:32:00,484 --> 01:32:02,118
Should we bow?

1365
01:32:02,119 --> 01:32:03,786
Yeah, he's a king.

1366
01:32:03,787 --> 01:32:05,788
Seems like I'm always
thanking you for something.

1367
01:32:06,925 --> 01:32:09,091
What are you doing?

1368
01:32:09,094 --> 01:32:11,226
Uh, we don't do that here.

1369
01:32:11,229 --> 01:32:13,761
So how big of an assault
should we expect?

1370
01:32:13,764 --> 01:32:16,899
Uh, sir, I think you should
expect quite a big assault.

1371
01:32:16,902 --> 01:32:17,966
How we looking?

1372
01:32:17,969 --> 01:32:20,003
You will have my Kingsguard,

1373
01:32:20,006 --> 01:32:23,939
the Border Tribe,
the Dora Milaje, and...

1374
01:32:23,940 --> 01:32:26,877
And a semi-stable
100-year-old man.

1375
01:32:29,779 --> 01:32:31,047
How you been, Buck?

1376
01:32:31,050 --> 01:32:34,152
Uh, not bad,
for the end of the world.

1377
01:32:46,198 --> 01:32:47,296
Whoa.

1378
01:32:47,298 --> 01:32:49,931
The structure is polymorphic.

1379
01:32:49,934 --> 01:32:53,167
Right, we had to attach
each neuron non-sequentially.

1380
01:32:53,170 --> 01:32:55,103
Why didn't you just reprogram

1381
01:32:55,104 --> 01:32:57,208
the synapses
to work collectively?

1382
01:32:58,275 --> 01:33:02,011
Because we didn't think of it.

1383
01:33:02,012 --> 01:33:03,378
I'm sure you did your best.

1384
01:33:03,381 --> 01:33:05,480
Can you do it?

1385
01:33:05,483 --> 01:33:09,051
Yes, but there are more than
two trillion neurons here.

1386
01:33:09,052 --> 01:33:12,488
One misalignment could cause
a cascade of circuit failures.

1387
01:33:12,489 --> 01:33:13,756
It will take time, brother.

1388
01:33:15,326 --> 01:33:16,426
How long?

1389
01:33:16,427 --> 01:33:17,859
As long as you can give me.

1390
01:33:22,332 --> 01:33:24,502
Something's entered
the atmosphere.

1391
01:33:41,385 --> 01:33:43,820
Hey, Cap, we got
a situation here.

1392
01:33:53,229 --> 01:33:54,829
God, I love this place.

1393
01:33:54,832 --> 01:33:56,998
Yeah, don't
start celebrating yet, guys.

1394
01:33:57,002 --> 01:33:58,935
We got more incoming
outside the dome.

1395
01:34:18,122 --> 01:34:19,189
It's too late.

1396
01:34:20,224 --> 01:34:22,090
We need to destroy
the stone now.

1397
01:34:22,091 --> 01:34:23,925
Vision, get your ass
back on the table.

1398
01:34:23,926 --> 01:34:25,327
We will hold them off.

1399
01:34:25,328 --> 01:34:28,997
Wanda, as soon as that stone's
out of his head...

1400
01:34:28,998 --> 01:34:30,001
you blow it to hell.

1401
01:34:30,333 --> 01:34:31,533
I will.

1402
01:34:31,534 --> 01:34:34,371
Evacuate the city.
Engage all defenses.

1403
01:34:35,171 --> 01:34:36,539
And get this man a shield.

1404
01:34:47,082 --> 01:34:48,216
I don't think

1405
01:34:48,217 --> 01:34:49,583
you get the scientifics here.

1406
01:34:49,586 --> 01:34:52,154
These rings are gigantic.
You wanna get them moving...

1407
01:34:52,155 --> 01:34:53,521
you're gonna need something
a lot bigger

1408
01:34:53,524 --> 01:34:54,889
to yank 'em loose.

1409
01:34:54,890 --> 01:34:57,057
- Leave that to me.
- Leave it to you?

1410
01:34:57,060 --> 01:35:00,228
Buddy, you're in space.
All you got is a rope and a...

1411
01:35:08,505 --> 01:35:09,570
Fire the engines!

1412
01:35:27,155 --> 01:35:29,891
More power, rabbit!

1413
01:36:01,256 --> 01:36:03,091
Well done, boy.

1414
01:36:04,728 --> 01:36:06,662
That's Nidavellir.

1415
01:36:26,716 --> 01:36:28,248
Damn it.

1416
01:36:28,251 --> 01:36:30,018
"Damn it"? What's "damn it"?

1417
01:36:30,020 --> 01:36:31,418
The mechanism
is crippled.

1418
01:36:31,421 --> 01:36:33,020
- What?
- With the iris closed,

1419
01:36:33,023 --> 01:36:34,188
I can't heat the metal.

1420
01:36:34,189 --> 01:36:35,989
How long will it take
to heat it?

1421
01:36:35,992 --> 01:36:38,293
A few minutes,
maybe more. Why?

1422
01:36:40,296 --> 01:36:41,462
I'm gonna hold it open.

1423
01:36:41,463 --> 01:36:42,695
That's suicide.

1424
01:36:42,698 --> 01:36:45,234
So is facing Thanos
without that axe.

1425
01:36:55,076 --> 01:36:56,042
How we looking, Bruce?

1426
01:36:56,045 --> 01:36:57,979
Yeah, I think
I'm getting the hang of it.

1427
01:37:01,216 --> 01:37:03,350
Wow! This is amazing, man.

1428
01:37:03,351 --> 01:37:05,351
It's like being the Hulk
without actually...

1429
01:37:09,157 --> 01:37:11,327
I'm okay. I'm okay.

1430
01:37:12,728 --> 01:37:13,793
I've got two heat signatures

1431
01:37:13,796 --> 01:37:14,996
breaking through
the tree line.

1432
01:37:43,358 --> 01:37:46,059
Thank you
for standing with us.

1433
01:38:07,515 --> 01:38:09,817
Where's your other friend?

1434
01:38:09,819 --> 01:38:12,319
You will pay for his life
with yours.

1435
01:38:13,320 --> 01:38:16,288
Thanos will have that stone.

1436
01:38:16,291 --> 01:38:17,791
That's not gonna happen.

1437
01:38:17,792 --> 01:38:20,359
You are in Wakanda now.

1438
01:38:20,362 --> 01:38:23,731
Thanos will have nothing
but dust and blood.

1439
01:38:27,135 --> 01:38:29,101
We have blood to spare.

1440
01:38:40,381 --> 01:38:41,815
They surrender?

1441
01:38:42,650 --> 01:38:43,716
Not exactly.

1442
01:39:10,679 --> 01:39:12,212
What the hell?

1443
01:39:15,181 --> 01:39:16,748
Looks like we pissed her off.

1444
01:39:27,494 --> 01:39:29,128
They're killing themselves.

1445
01:40:05,332 --> 01:40:06,865
You see the teeth
on those things?

1446
01:40:06,868 --> 01:40:07,934
All right, back up, Sam.

1447
01:40:07,935 --> 01:40:09,296
You're gonna get
your wings singed.

1448
01:40:21,547 --> 01:40:22,948
Cap, if these things
circle the perimeter

1449
01:40:22,951 --> 01:40:24,082
and get in behind us...

1450
01:40:24,085 --> 01:40:26,451
there's nothing
between them and Vision.

1451
01:40:26,453 --> 01:40:28,420
Then we better keep 'em
in front of us.

1452
01:40:28,421 --> 01:40:29,689
How do we do that?

1453
01:40:31,993 --> 01:40:33,694
We open the barrier.

1454
01:40:35,896 --> 01:40:40,465
On my signal, open North-West
Section Seventeen.

1455
01:40:40,466 --> 01:40:42,434
Requesting
confirmation, My King.

1456
01:40:42,435 --> 01:40:44,301
You said open the barrier?

1457
01:40:44,304 --> 01:40:45,671
On my signal.

1458
01:40:45,672 --> 01:40:47,573
This will be
the end of Wakanda.

1459
01:40:48,841 --> 01:40:52,378
Then it will be
the noblest ending in history.

1460
01:41:05,259 --> 01:41:06,792
Wakanda forever!

1461
01:41:19,273 --> 01:41:20,274
Now!

1462
01:41:50,537 --> 01:41:52,003
How much longer, Shuri?

1463
01:41:52,006 --> 01:41:53,771
I've barely begun, brother.

1464
01:41:53,774 --> 01:41:55,641
You might want to pick up
the pace.

1465
01:42:02,682 --> 01:42:04,716
Allfathers, give me strength.

1466
01:42:04,717 --> 01:42:06,685
You understand, boy?

1467
01:42:06,686 --> 01:42:09,689
You're about to take
the full force of a star.

1468
01:42:10,657 --> 01:42:12,724
It'll kill you.

1469
01:42:12,725 --> 01:42:14,895
Only if I die.

1470
01:42:15,328 --> 01:42:16,728
Yes.

1471
01:42:16,729 --> 01:42:19,532
That's what killing you means.

1472
01:42:47,527 --> 01:42:49,462
Hold it! Hold it, Thor!

1473
01:43:39,845 --> 01:43:41,814
Thor! Say something. Come on.

1474
01:43:42,747 --> 01:43:43,748
Thor, you okay?

1475
01:43:49,488 --> 01:43:50,854
I think he's dying.

1476
01:43:50,856 --> 01:43:52,824
He needs the axe!

1477
01:43:54,193 --> 01:43:55,661
Where's the handle?

1478
01:43:58,698 --> 01:44:00,966
Tree, help me find the handle!

1479
01:45:09,868 --> 01:45:12,037
There's too many of 'em!

1480
01:45:38,630 --> 01:45:41,965
You guys
are so screwed now!

1481
01:45:45,203 --> 01:45:47,270
Bring me Thanos!

1482
01:46:20,006 --> 01:46:21,604
Oh, yeah.

1483
01:46:24,708 --> 01:46:26,711
You're much more of a Thanos.

1484
01:46:28,979 --> 01:46:31,115
I take it the Maw is dead.

1485
01:46:33,350 --> 01:46:35,920
This day
extracts a heavy toll.

1486
01:46:37,688 --> 01:46:40,189
Still, he accomplished
his mission.

1487
01:46:40,190 --> 01:46:41,792
You may regret that.

1488
01:46:42,658 --> 01:46:44,028
He brought you face-to-face

1489
01:46:44,029 --> 01:46:45,561
with the Master
of the Mystic Arts.

1490
01:46:48,698 --> 01:46:51,069
And where do you think
he brought you?

1491
01:46:52,136 --> 01:46:54,905
Let me guess. Your home?

1492
01:46:59,210 --> 01:47:00,644
It was.

1493
01:47:03,247 --> 01:47:04,782
And it was beautiful.

1494
01:47:07,284 --> 01:47:09,984
Titan was like most planets.

1495
01:47:09,987 --> 01:47:13,021
Too many mouths,
not enough to go around.

1496
01:47:13,024 --> 01:47:16,226
And when we faced extinction,
I offered a solution.

1497
01:47:17,228 --> 01:47:19,162
Genocide.

1498
01:47:19,163 --> 01:47:23,234
But random, dispassionate,
fair to rich and poor alike.

1499
01:47:24,701 --> 01:47:27,403
They called me a madman.

1500
01:47:27,404 --> 01:47:29,806
And what I predicted
came to pass.

1501
01:47:32,377 --> 01:47:34,578
Congratulations,
you're a prophet.

1502
01:47:35,046 --> 01:47:36,345
I'm a survivor.

1503
01:47:36,346 --> 01:47:38,846
Who wants to murder trillions.

1504
01:47:38,849 --> 01:47:43,051
With all six stones, I could
simply snap my fingers.

1505
01:47:43,052 --> 01:47:47,824
They would all cease to exist.
I call that mercy.

1506
01:47:49,893 --> 01:47:51,295
And then what?

1507
01:47:52,762 --> 01:47:54,996
I'd finally rest...

1508
01:47:54,997 --> 01:47:59,234
and watch the sun rise
on a grateful universe.

1509
01:47:59,235 --> 01:48:03,738
The hardest choices require
the strongest wills.

1510
01:48:03,739 --> 01:48:08,311
I think you'll find our will
equal to yours.

1511
01:48:09,846 --> 01:48:10,847
Our?

1512
01:48:16,920 --> 01:48:18,386
Piece of cake, Quill.

1513
01:48:18,387 --> 01:48:20,791
Yeah, if your goal
was to piss him off.

1514
01:48:58,929 --> 01:49:00,295
Boom!

1515
01:49:00,296 --> 01:49:03,065
Don't let him close his fist.

1516
01:49:07,237 --> 01:49:08,238
Magic.

1517
01:49:08,938 --> 01:49:09,939
More magic.

1518
01:49:10,805 --> 01:49:11,806
Magic with a kick.

1519
01:49:12,309 --> 01:49:13,310
Magic with a...

1520
01:49:14,777 --> 01:49:16,012
Insect!

1521
01:49:53,350 --> 01:49:54,782
Well, well.

1522
01:49:54,783 --> 01:49:55,949
You should've killed me.

1523
01:49:55,952 --> 01:49:57,784
It would've been
a waste of parts!

1524
01:50:03,225 --> 01:50:04,390
Where's Gamora?

1525
01:50:45,600 --> 01:50:46,966
Is he under?
Don't let up.

1526
01:50:46,969 --> 01:50:49,603
Be quick. He is very strong.

1527
01:50:49,604 --> 01:50:51,971
Parker, help! Get over here.

1528
01:50:51,974 --> 01:50:54,243
She can't hold him
much longer. Let's go.

1529
01:50:59,614 --> 01:51:00,948
We gotta open
his fingers to get it off.

1530
01:51:00,949 --> 01:51:02,115
I thought you'd be
hard to catch.

1531
01:51:02,118 --> 01:51:03,398
For the record,
this was my plan.

1532
01:51:04,552 --> 01:51:06,322
You're not so strong now, huh?

1533
01:51:06,921 --> 01:51:08,588
Where is Gamora?

1534
01:51:08,591 --> 01:51:10,890
My Gamora.

1535
01:51:10,891 --> 01:51:13,159
No, bullshit!

1536
01:51:13,162 --> 01:51:14,396
Where is she?

1537
01:51:15,463 --> 01:51:16,898
He is in anguish.

1538
01:51:17,466 --> 01:51:19,533
Good.

1539
01:51:19,534 --> 01:51:22,435
He... He mourns.

1540
01:51:22,438 --> 01:51:26,141
What does
this monster have to mourn?

1541
01:51:26,908 --> 01:51:27,975
Gamora.

1542
01:51:31,880 --> 01:51:33,212
What?

1543
01:51:33,215 --> 01:51:35,315
He took her to Vormir.

1544
01:51:35,318 --> 01:51:37,286
He came back
with the Soul Stone.

1545
01:51:38,118 --> 01:51:39,521
But she didn't.

1546
01:51:41,457 --> 01:51:45,492
Okay, Quill, you gotta cool it
right now. You understand?

1547
01:51:45,493 --> 01:51:49,064
Don't, don't. Don't engage.
We almost got this off!

1548
01:51:50,265 --> 01:51:51,266
Tell me she's lying.

1549
01:51:53,636 --> 01:51:56,471
Asshole,
tell me you didn't do it!

1550
01:51:58,039 --> 01:52:01,377
I had to.

1551
01:52:02,176 --> 01:52:03,577
No, you didn't.

1552
01:52:03,578 --> 01:52:05,413
No, you didn't.

1553
01:52:09,283 --> 01:52:10,684
- No, you didn't!
- Quill!

1554
01:52:10,685 --> 01:52:13,286
Hey, stop!
Hey, stop! Stop!

1555
01:52:13,287 --> 01:52:14,520
Hey, stop! Stop!

1556
01:52:14,523 --> 01:52:16,764
It's coming, it's
coming. I got it, I got it!

1557
01:52:19,961 --> 01:52:20,962
Oh, God.

1558
01:53:19,354 --> 01:53:23,055
Come and get some,
space dogs!

1559
01:53:25,693 --> 01:53:28,493
Come on! Get some! Get some!

1560
01:53:28,496 --> 01:53:30,630
Come on! Get some!

1561
01:53:30,631 --> 01:53:33,365
- How much for the gun?
- Not for sale.

1562
01:53:33,368 --> 01:53:35,270
Okay. How much for the arm?

1563
01:53:37,171 --> 01:53:39,238
Oh, I'll get that arm.

1564
01:53:48,081 --> 01:53:49,381
New haircut?

1565
01:53:49,384 --> 01:53:50,618
Noticed you've copied
my beard.

1566
01:53:53,119 --> 01:53:55,122
By the way, this is
a friend of mine, Tree.

1567
01:53:56,055 --> 01:53:57,990
I am Groot.

1568
01:53:58,792 --> 01:54:00,693
I am Steve Rogers.

1569
01:54:20,413 --> 01:54:22,550
Fall back! Fall back, now!

1570
01:54:32,091 --> 01:54:34,326
Focus that fire
on the left flank, Sam.

1571
01:54:34,328 --> 01:54:35,429
I'm doing it.

1572
01:54:59,353 --> 01:55:01,054
Why was she up there
all this time?

1573
01:55:01,823 --> 01:55:04,725
She's on the field. Take it.

1574
01:55:36,422 --> 01:55:38,590
Guys, we got
a Vision situation here.

1575
01:55:41,328 --> 01:55:43,427
Somebody get to Vision!

1576
01:55:43,430 --> 01:55:45,265
- I got him!
- On my way.

1577
01:55:50,570 --> 01:55:53,572
He'll die alone. As will you.

1578
01:55:53,573 --> 01:55:54,807
She's not alone.

1579
01:56:21,199 --> 01:56:22,900
Oh, no, you don't.

1580
01:56:22,903 --> 01:56:24,603
This isn't gonna be
like New York, pal.

1581
01:56:24,604 --> 01:56:27,171
This suit's already kicked
the crap outta the Hulk.

1582
01:56:27,172 --> 01:56:28,238
What? No! No!

1583
01:56:31,778 --> 01:56:34,547
Guys!
Vision needs backup, now!

1584
01:56:36,550 --> 01:56:38,282
Hulk? Hulk,

1585
01:56:38,283 --> 01:56:40,350
I know you like making your
entrance at the last second.

1586
01:56:40,353 --> 01:56:42,855
Well, this is it, man.
This is the last, last second.

1587
01:56:47,426 --> 01:56:48,862
Hulk! Hulk!

1588
01:56:49,762 --> 01:56:50,764
Hulk!

1589
01:56:51,898 --> 01:56:54,364
No!

1590
01:56:54,367 --> 01:56:57,301
Oh, screw
you, you big, green asshole!

1591
01:56:57,302 --> 01:56:58,470
I'll do it myself!

1592
01:56:59,404 --> 01:57:01,273
Come on! Yeah!

1593
01:57:13,551 --> 01:57:15,284
See ya!

1594
01:57:26,666 --> 01:57:29,332
Hulk, we got a lot
to figure out, pal.

1595
01:57:40,311 --> 01:57:42,213
I thought you were formidable,
machine.

1596
01:57:42,981 --> 01:57:45,618
But you're dying,
like any man.

1597
01:57:54,292 --> 01:57:55,493
Get outta here!

1598
01:57:58,831 --> 01:57:59,864
Go!

1599
01:58:18,650 --> 01:58:20,386
That was really gross.

1600
01:58:47,511 --> 01:58:48,591
I thought I told you to go.

1601
01:58:50,050 --> 01:58:52,018
We don't trade lives, Captain.

1602
01:59:03,427 --> 01:59:05,661
I got you. I got you.

1603
01:59:05,662 --> 01:59:07,664
I'm sorry I can't remember
anybody's names.

1604
01:59:52,877 --> 01:59:54,543
You're full of tricks, wizard.

1605
01:59:56,547 --> 01:59:59,484
Yet you never once used
your greatest weapon.

1606
02:00:02,820 --> 02:00:03,886
A fake.

1607
02:00:11,796 --> 02:00:15,497
You throw another moon at me,
and I'm gonna lose it.

1608
02:00:15,500 --> 02:00:16,765
Stark.

1609
02:00:16,768 --> 02:00:17,836
You know me?

1610
02:00:18,536 --> 02:00:20,069
I do.

1611
02:00:20,070 --> 02:00:23,373
You're not the only one
cursed with knowledge.

1612
02:00:24,108 --> 02:00:25,577
My only curse is you.

1613
02:00:28,046 --> 02:00:29,047
Come on!

1614
02:00:57,009 --> 02:00:58,976
All that for a drop of blood.

1615
02:01:43,021 --> 02:01:44,854
You have my respect, Stark.

1616
02:01:46,590 --> 02:01:49,760
When I'm done, half of
humanity will still be alive.

1617
02:01:55,166 --> 02:01:57,434
I hope they remember you.

1618
02:02:07,077 --> 02:02:08,177
Stop.

1619
02:02:14,618 --> 02:02:15,618
Spare his life...

1620
02:02:17,253 --> 02:02:19,055
and I will give you the stone.

1621
02:02:22,693 --> 02:02:23,926
No tricks.

1622
02:02:28,765 --> 02:02:29,765
Don't.

1623
02:03:21,118 --> 02:03:22,886
One to go.

1624
02:03:32,795 --> 02:03:34,131
Where is he?

1625
02:03:43,105 --> 02:03:44,606
Did we just lose?

1626
02:03:48,345 --> 02:03:50,279
Why would you do that?

1627
02:03:53,748 --> 02:03:55,951
We're in the endgame now.

1628
02:04:20,775 --> 02:04:23,344
Are you okay?

1629
02:04:25,247 --> 02:04:27,081
What? What is it?

1630
02:04:29,150 --> 02:04:30,252
He's here.

1631
02:04:41,262 --> 02:04:44,300
Everyone, on my position.
We have incoming.

1632
02:04:47,103 --> 02:04:49,070
What the hell?

1633
02:05:14,697 --> 02:05:15,698
Cap.

1634
02:05:16,297 --> 02:05:17,867
That's him.

1635
02:05:19,902 --> 02:05:22,371
Eyes up. Stay sharp.

1636
02:05:46,962 --> 02:05:47,962
Wanda.

1637
02:05:49,064 --> 02:05:50,430
It's time.

1638
02:05:50,431 --> 02:05:51,764
No.

1639
02:05:51,765 --> 02:05:54,067
They can't stop him, Wanda,
but we can.

1640
02:05:54,069 --> 02:05:55,734
Look at me.

1641
02:05:55,737 --> 02:05:56,935
You have the power
to destroy the stone.

1642
02:05:56,938 --> 02:05:58,005
Don't.

1643
02:05:58,006 --> 02:05:59,207
You must do it. Wanda, please.

1644
02:06:01,109 --> 02:06:03,778
We are out of time.

1645
02:06:04,412 --> 02:06:05,845
I can't.

1646
02:06:05,846 --> 02:06:07,182
Yes, you can.

1647
02:06:07,916 --> 02:06:09,118
You can.

1648
02:06:10,519 --> 02:06:12,953
If he gets the stone,
half the universe dies.

1649
02:06:15,256 --> 02:06:16,858
It's not fair.

1650
02:06:18,027 --> 02:06:19,694
It shouldn't be you,
but it is.

1651
02:06:21,462 --> 02:06:23,032
It's all right.

1652
02:06:24,365 --> 02:06:26,134
You could never hurt me.

1653
02:06:35,176 --> 02:06:37,011
I just feel you.

1654
02:08:00,127 --> 02:08:01,229
It's all right.

1655
02:08:11,171 --> 02:08:12,439
It's all right.

1656
02:08:16,909 --> 02:08:17,978
I love you.

1657
02:08:47,239 --> 02:08:49,342
I understand, my child.

1658
02:08:50,976 --> 02:08:52,479
Better than anyone.

1659
02:08:54,213 --> 02:08:56,149
You could never.

1660
02:09:01,021 --> 02:09:04,024
Today, I lost more
than you can know.

1661
02:09:05,659 --> 02:09:08,362
But now is no time to mourn.

1662
02:09:10,564 --> 02:09:14,568
Now is no time at all.

1663
02:09:38,024 --> 02:09:39,025
No!

1664
02:10:37,016 --> 02:10:38,385
I told you...

1665
02:10:39,719 --> 02:10:41,555
you'd die for that.

1666
02:10:56,036 --> 02:10:57,636
You should have...

1667
02:11:00,338 --> 02:11:01,707
You should...

1668
02:11:04,310 --> 02:11:07,514
You should have
gone for the head.

1669
02:11:09,448 --> 02:11:10,448
No!

1670
02:11:43,782 --> 02:11:45,149
Daughter?

1671
02:11:52,658 --> 02:11:54,158
Did you do it?

1672
02:11:56,095 --> 02:11:57,095
Yes.

1673
02:12:05,436 --> 02:12:07,105
What did it cost?

1674
02:12:10,676 --> 02:12:12,278
Everything.

1675
02:12:22,488 --> 02:12:24,122
What did you do?

1676
02:12:25,323 --> 02:12:26,725
What'd you do?

1677
02:12:40,439 --> 02:12:41,739
Where'd he go?

1678
02:12:44,676 --> 02:12:45,841
Thor.

1679
02:12:49,180 --> 02:12:50,814
Where'd he go?

1680
02:12:50,815 --> 02:12:52,216
Steve?

1681
02:13:26,885 --> 02:13:29,786
Up, General. Up!

1682
02:13:29,787 --> 02:13:31,386
This is no place to die.

1683
02:13:46,371 --> 02:13:47,904
I am Groot.

1684
02:13:47,905 --> 02:13:49,539
Oh...

1685
02:13:50,440 --> 02:13:52,510
No, no, no!

1686
02:13:53,377 --> 02:13:56,247
Groot! No.

1687
02:14:09,594 --> 02:14:10,728
Sam!

1688
02:14:14,765 --> 02:14:16,466
Sam, where you at?

1689
02:14:25,743 --> 02:14:27,912
Something's happening.

1690
02:14:40,024 --> 02:14:41,359
Quill?

1691
02:14:48,666 --> 02:14:49,931
Steady, Quill.

1692
02:14:49,934 --> 02:14:51,234
Oh, man.

1693
02:14:55,372 --> 02:14:56,373
Tony.

1694
02:14:59,810 --> 02:15:02,380
There was no other way.

1695
02:15:07,918 --> 02:15:08,920
Mr. Stark?

1696
02:15:13,490 --> 02:15:14,759
I don't feel so good.

1697
02:15:16,828 --> 02:15:17,726
You're all right.

1698
02:15:17,729 --> 02:15:19,029
I don't... I don't know
what's happening.

1699
02:15:19,030 --> 02:15:20,664
I don't know...

1700
02:15:22,466 --> 02:15:23,599
I don't want to go.

1701
02:15:23,600 --> 02:15:25,500
I don't want to go, sir.
Please.

1702
02:15:25,502 --> 02:15:28,270
Please, I don't want to go.
I don't want to go.

1703
02:15:32,710 --> 02:15:34,310
I'm sorry.

1704
02:15:48,993 --> 02:15:50,560
He did it.

1705
02:16:15,385 --> 02:16:18,555
What is this?
What the hell is happening?

1706
02:16:35,471 --> 02:16:37,073
Oh, God.

1707
02:27:33,424 --> 02:27:35,024
Still no word
from Stark?

1708
02:27:35,027 --> 02:27:36,358
No, not yet.

1709
02:27:36,360 --> 02:27:37,460
We're watching every satellite

1710
02:27:37,462 --> 02:27:39,629
on both hemispheres,
but still nothing.

1711
02:27:39,630 --> 02:27:41,730
What is it?

1712
02:27:41,733 --> 02:27:44,333
Multiple bogeys
over Wakanda.

1713
02:27:44,334 --> 02:27:46,402
Same energy signature
as New York?

1714
02:27:46,404 --> 02:27:47,673
Ten times bigger.

1715
02:27:49,272 --> 02:27:50,439
Tell Klein
we'll meet him at...

1716
02:27:50,441 --> 02:27:51,540
Nick! Nick!

1717
02:28:05,189 --> 02:28:06,424
They okay?

1718
02:28:07,424 --> 02:28:09,290
There's no one here.

1719
02:28:18,668 --> 02:28:20,271
Call Control.

1720
02:28:21,072 --> 02:28:22,306
Code red.

1721
02:28:22,841 --> 02:28:24,041
Nick.

1722
02:28:25,575 --> 02:28:26,576
Hill.

1723
02:28:41,525 --> 02:28:42,659
Oh, no.

1724
02:28:44,361 --> 02:28:45,362
Mother...

1725
02:29:06,027 --> 02:29:11,031
Subtitles by explosiveskull
Resync by GoldenBeard

